title: tabouli(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Should be prepared at least 3 hours before serving to allow to thoroughly marinate and chill.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken oklahoma
directions: Boil chicken; when done, debone and cut into pieces.
Oil a casserole dish and place ingredients into dish in this order: mushroom soup, asparagus, chicken, mushrooms, chicken soup, Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 300° until cheeses melt and casserole is bubbly.

title: superb fudge cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa, water and oil to a boil.
Add flour and sugar and mix.
Add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and baking soda. Pour into a greased jelly roll pan or 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: italian ham lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; set aside.
Cook spinach; set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large pan, combine milk, cornstarch and onion. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in yogurt.
Spread 2 tablespoons of yogurt sauce on bottom of 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Stir ham and Italian seasoning into remaining sauce.
Layer noodles, then sauce, then spinach.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Repeat another layer of noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes; 270 calories, 9 g. fat and 50 mg. cholesterol.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Spread dough onto large jelly roll pan.
Spread oil evenly over dough; sprinkle with corn meal.
Brown ground meat with chopped onion; drain well.
Add the refried beans, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Mix.
Spread meat mixture over dough.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°, or until crust browns.
Top with grated cheese.
Return to oven for 2 minutes to melt cheese.

title: south of the border spaghetti(quick casserole)
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and cook, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce, salt, pepper, green chilies and chili powder.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook vermicelli; drain. Combine sauce and vermicelli.
Layer half the vermicelli mixture in a 3-quart baking dish.
Cover with half the cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese with electric mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Mix all together and top with maraschino cherries if desired. Place in refrigerator.

title: picante chicken
directions: Place a small amount of picante sauce in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan to prevent chicken from sticking.
Place chicken pieces in pan.

title: fresh fruit bowl
directions: Fresh fruit can be :
strawberries, pitted cherries, seedless grapes, cantaloupe or watermelon balls, plums, bananas, peaches, nectarines or kiwi.

title: sweet and sour beets
directions: Cook beets until tender then slice and cut into bite size pieces.
Combine water, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour over beets; let stand overnight.
To can, cold pack 5 to 10 minutes.

title: molded cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumber, salt, pimento and lemon juice. Soak gelatin in cold water 5 minutes. Dissolve over hot water and mix thoroughly with whipped cream. Add cucumber mixture and pour into mold.
Chill.

title: cranberry salad 2
directions: Warm orange juice.
Mix jello and orange juice.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into mold.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add the sour cream and eggs, beating well.
Mix the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add to the mixture, beating well.
Add the vanilla.

title: nana's stuffed wieners
directions: Boil wieners 4 or 5 minutes; drain and cool.
Prepare mashed potatoes as you would to serve.
When wieners are cool, split almost through lengthwise.
Stuff with mashed potatoes; sprinkle cheese on top.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Turn oven on broil; broil until cheese melts.

title: boiled custard
directions: Heat milk in double boiler just to boiling point.
Beat eggs and sugar, blend them well.
Add to milk; cook until it coats a spoon good.
Stir constantly while cooking.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and chill.

title: savory party mix
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup melted butter, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Drizzle over the remaining mixture which has been placed on a cookie sheet.
Toss well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir twice.

title: seafood chowder
directions: In a large cookpot, melt butter on medium heat.
Add onion (leek), pepper and celery.
Cook until tender (5 to 10 minutes). Add parsley.
Blend in flour and stir 1 minute.
Add chicken stock and water; blend.
Add potatoes and simmer, covered, until tender. Add seasoning.
Add seafood and stir.
Add milk and bring to a simmer on medium to low heat.
Do not boil.
Add salt to taste. Sprinkle with chopped fresh parsley before serving.

title: senator soup
directions: In a large stock pot, cook ham bone or hocks until tender in 3 quarts of water.
Remove from pot and take off any good meat.
Add all other ingredients, including beans that have been soaked overnight and drained.
Cook until beans get very soft.
For a creamier soup, take about 3 cups of beans out and put in blender or beat with a mixer.
Return mixture to soup and turn to simmer until ready to serve.

title: sauced carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain and set aside.
Dice and saute in butter or oleo remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, do not overcook. Pour over carrots.
Let stand to blend flavor.
Reheat to serve.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix undrained pineapple with pudding; add Cool Whip.
Stir in marshmallows.
Pour into square dish.
Cool until set.

title: ice cream pumpkin pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into crumb crust. Freeze.
Before serving, take out of freezer a short time before.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
(For a softer, rounder cookie, add 1/2 cup more flour.) Drop by rounded teaspoon 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: fried carrots
directions: Brown diced onion in skillet.
Cook carrot slices in salted water until almost done.
Add carrot slices to browned bacon.
Also add a small amount of carrot liquid.
Combine salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over carrots.
Cover and fry until done.

title: gooey-gooey cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions. While still warm, punch holes 1-inch apart with wooden spoon handle but not all the way through. Pour milk into holes. Pour topping over the cake. Refrigerate. When cool, top with Cool Whip and crushed candy bars. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chili dip
directions: In an oblong Pyrex dish, spread cream cheese on bottom of dish.
Spread chili on top.
Cut cheese into small cubes and sprinkle evenly over chili.
Microwave on Medium power until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pork chop with pizzaz
directions: In skillet, brown chops.
Pour off fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add broth, water and pepper sauce.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and noodles.
Cook 15 minutes more or until done.
Stir often.

title: international cheese melt(it's worth yelling about)
directions: Combine cheeses, garlic and basil in 6-inch cast-iron frypan or heavy ovenproof casserole. (You can use a larger pan or casserole for several people, individual servings are really necessary for this.)
Pop into a 350° oven until cheese has melted smoothly.
Toss the bread slices onto the rack along with the pan of cheese.
Toast for 1 minute on each side.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix well; pour into 9 x 15-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tomato and saffron chicken
directions: Wash and pat chicken dry.
Sprinkle with salt and freshly ground pepper.
Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons of olive oil in a deep, heavy skillet, large enough to hold the chicken in a single layer. Lightly brown chicken in the hot oil, about 3 minutes on each side.
Transfer chicken to a towel-lined plate.

title: champagne cocktail
directions: Stir all ingredients in large punch bowl and add 1 tray of ice.
Delicious.
Caution advised.

title: birthday punch
directions: Mix sugar and 1 quart of water. Bring to a boil, then let it cool. In a separate container, mix lemon juice, orange juice, pineapple juice and 1 gallon water. Add sugar syrup. Chill. Add chilled ginger ale just before serving. Serves 50.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add 1/3 cup sour cream (or yogurt), salt, pepper, sugar and oleo.
Add just enough milk to proper consistency and beat until fluffy.
Add dill seed, chives or dry onion and cooked spinach (well drained and chopped).
Place in greased casserole and top with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend 2 minutes.
Use Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: crisp sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain brine from pickles. Slice pickles into 3/8-inch slices. Place in bowl.
In empty jar, place vinegar and spices. Return pickle slices to jar and pour sugar over top. Do not stir. Refrigerate 10 days before eating.
For a second batch, you may use the same liquid adding 1 cup sugar only.

title: elvis presley's favorite pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar together.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into mixing bowl.
Add cheese; mix well.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add enough cold water to make stiff dough.
Turn onto floured surface.
Roll to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut into strips.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons bacon grease in heavy skillet.
Crumble sausage into skillet and fry until well done.
With slotted spoon, remove sausage and drain on paper towel.
Measure pan drippings and, if needed, add enough bacon grease to make 4 tablespoons and return to skillet.
Add flour to grease and stir with fork to mix well.
Continue stirring over medium heat until flour is lightly browned.
Add milk and water.
Stir and heat until thickened.
Add sausage.
Serve over hot biscuits.
This can also be made with all milk or all water for the liquid.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Place by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Top with sugar or powdered sugar, nuts, colored sugar or your favorite topping.
Bake for 8 minutes or until cookies are solid to touch.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning. Mix beans with salsa. In large flat platter, layer first bean mix. Top with avocado mixture. Next, taco and mayonnaise mixture. Sprinkle with green onions and tomato and top with cheese. Chill. Serve with white corn chips.

title: white wine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except nuts, and mix together.
Spray Bundt pan and sprinkle nuts on bottom. Pour batter over nuts.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from oven and slowly pour 1/2 of glaze on cake.
Cool 15 minutes and turn out of pan. Spoon rest of glaze on warm cake.

title: easy drop dumplings for stew
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is of cornmeal consistency.
Add milk.
Mix lightly until soft dough is formed.
Drop from teaspoon into boiling stew. Cover tightly.
Cook without removing cover for 12 minutes.

title: hot wassail
directions: Put all the ingredients in a crock-pot and heat thoroughly. Remove the seasonings before serving.
Add rum if desired.

title: spice bars
directions: Combine oil, honey and	sugar and add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add
egg
and chopped pecans.
Press into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes (no longer).

title: green salsa
directions: Cook tomatillos, chilies and onions in water till tender. Add all other ingredients and mix in blender. Serve with chips, if desired.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add seasoning per package instructions. Put aside until ready to serve. Cut up lettuce and tomatoes. Put in a large bowl. Add shredded cheese.
Before serving, add hamburger and crushed Doritos.

title: coconut center bonbons
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat and add butter, flavoring and as much dry coconut as the syrup will absorb.
Cool on a large platter.
When cool enough to handle, make into small ball (3/4-inch).
Dip into chocolate or white almond bark coating.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour batter equally into 3 pans.
Bake for 20 minutes; cool.
Frost with:

title: spiced honey-mustard brie
directions: Remove rind from top of cheese to within 1/2 inch of edge. Place Brie in center of platter.
Spread honey mustard over top. Sprinkle with almonds.
Cover and let stand at room temperature 1 hour.
Toss apple wedges in juice.
When ready to serve, pat dry and serve at once with cheese.

title: ham and egg brunch
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Toss bread, ham and cheese evenly on bottom.
Beat eggs until foamy; beat in milk and mustard.
Pour eggs over bread mixture.
Cover tightly with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: new orleans spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain well.
Slightly saute onion, garlic and green pepper in butter.
Add ground meat, tomato soup, paprika, cayenne pepper and salt.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and 1/4 cup of cheese.
Mix cooked spaghetti in with the ground meat sauce.
Spoon into baking dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven. Serves 5 to 8.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and drop by a teaspoonful into hot oil (preferably oil that you have fried fish in).
Dough will rise to top of oil.
Turn once if the hush puppies don't turn themselves.

title: doyle's corn chowder
directions: Mix altogether and serve.

title: taco pie (to be used as a dip for nachos)
directions: Brown and drain beef, add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Place in bottom of shallow dish and (9 x 13-inch is fine).
Allow to cool.
Layer sour cream over ground beef.
Layer refried beans over sour cream.
Melt Velveeta and add drained Ro-Tel to Velveeta cheese.
Pour this over refried beans; top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with green onions and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips or nachos. Delicious!

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: classic onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter and oil until tender.
Add broth, sugar and nutmeg.
Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 10 minutes.
Ladle into baking dish.
Top with bread and 2 Tbsp. cheese.
Bake at 300 degrees for 10 minutes.
Makes 9 cups.

title: one cup excellent cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add egg and beat until well mixed.
Mix together flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture and beat until well blended.
Stir in the remaining ingredients in the order given.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 10 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: ye olde curiosity shoppe cake 'n' frosting
directions: Cream as follows:
First, cream the margarine until fluffy; stir in cocoa.
Sift sugar and add gradually to creamed mixture, beating constantly.
Stir in enough milk to make the right consistency for spreading.
One can add 1 egg yolk and beat in well at this time, if desired, for extra smoothness.
Stir in salt and vanilla.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: bechamel sauce for onion pie
directions: Melt butter and gradually add milk, flour, salt and pepper. Cook a little.
Set aside.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg, water and vanilla; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips; mix thoroughly. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes, or until tests done. Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: Cook onion in salad oil until golden.
Add all other ingredients except the corned beef.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add corned beef and simmer an additional 10 minutes or until it thickens.

title: pistachio ice cream cake
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup cracker crumbs. Mix rest of crumbs and butter and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine pudding mix and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Combine Cool Whip and ice cream and add to the pudding mixture.
Combine until smooth.
Pour into the cracker crust.
Freeze until firm. Makes 12 servings.

title: dutch hutspot
directions: Stir vegetables together and put with herbs and oil in a casserole.
Cook in hot oven for an hour.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cut up chicken into bite-size pieces and brown with stick of butter, olive oil, parsley and garlic.
Remove chicken.
Add 1 cup sour cream to frypan and stir.
Put cooked ziti and cooked broccoli into casserole dish.
Add chicken.
Pour frypan mixture over this.
Add 2 bags Parmesan cheese.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted throughout.

title: homemade fudgy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over very low heat until just melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix until well blended.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool and cut in squares.
Makes 24.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef in fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer a half hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches and cut in thirds; do not use juice.
Add strawberries that have been cut in slices.
Add banana slices. Pour in pineapple and juice.
Sprinkle Tang mix over fruit mixture.
Add dry pudding mix to fruit and mix well.
Make early in the morning to serve that night.
Chill all day.
Each 1/2 cup serving is 12 calories.

title: tacos
directions: Cook and stir hamburger meat in skillet until light brown. Stir in taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered stirring occasionally until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Spoon 1/4 cup hamburger mixture into each shell. Top with tomatoes, lettuce and shredded cheese.

title: polish sausage and sauerkraut
directions: Layer in baking dish in order listed.
Bake 1 hour at 325° or until heated well.

title: kahlua brownies
directions: Sift flour together with baking powder and salt.
Melt chocolate and butter over very low heat.
Beat eggs with sugar until light.
Stir in chocolate mixture and Kahlua.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Turn into greased 9-inch square pan lined on bottom with foil.
Bake for about 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until top springs back when touched.
Cool in pan; cut in squares.

title: party meatballs(sounds a bit strange, but very good and easy)
directions: Form meat into 1-inch balls and brown
in skillet.
Or put in metal or glass baking pan and bake at 375° until done (about 20 minutes), or microwave for 5 minutes on High.
In large saucepan, melt jelly and add other ingredients.
Drain fat from meatballs and add to sauce.
Simmer for an hour or longer (tastes better the longer it cooks!)
Serve in a crock-pot.
This sauce is also terrific with miniature smoked sausages.

title: janelle's barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add onions and saute until lightly brown. Then add rest of ingredients.
Boil slowly 15 minutes or until thick and glossy.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups sauce.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Place 1 package of crescent rolls on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Fry hamburger until browned with onion soup mix. Drain off fat.
Mix hamburger with egg and cheese.
Spread on top of crescent rolls.
Place the other package of crescent rolls on top.
Bake at 370° for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for another 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine
all
ingredients except bread crumbs and place in casserole.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: eclair torte
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat butter and water to boiling. Stir in flour all at once, over low heat.
Beat until ball is formed.
Beat in eggs, one at a time until smooth.
Can be done by hand or with a mixer.
Drop by large spoonfuls onto very lightly greased cookie sheet to form a circle.
(I grease just a ring about 9-inch diameter.)
Bake at 400° for 50-55 minutes (be sure it is well browned or it may flatten while cooling).
Cool away from drafts.
Slice off top and remove some of the thicker strings with a fork.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: *Note:
If using canned peaches, drain well and omit extra cup of sugar.

title: decorated vanilla butter cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy; blend in vanilla extract.
Add egg; beat for one minute.
Stir in flour gradually.
Cover; refrigerate for 2 hours. Roll out on board, floured, to 1/4-inch thickness; cut out in desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Decorate with frosting.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Add pizza sauce and soup.
Mix well and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add noodles and mix thoroughly.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute stems and onion in butter.
Add milk; stir until thick (10 minutes).
Stuff and bake at 325° for 5
to 10 minutes.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Grind together bologna and cheese and set aside.
Brown hamburger and onion; let cool.
Stir in bologna mixture, spaghetti sauce, parsley flakes, salt and oregano.
Split buns.
Place about 2 tablespoons of mixture on each bun half.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° or until cheese is melted.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Stir together corn, flour, sugar, salt, pepper and milk in bowl.
Fold in beaten egg yolks, then put in egg whites.
Pour into buttered dish, then top with butter.
Bake, uncovered for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: stew the old fashioned way
directions: In a Ziploc type bag, put flour and desired salt and pepper. You will want enough to shake all your stew meat.
Shake 4-5 pieces at a time and brown in skillet with hot oil.
In your stew pot (or Dutch oven) mix the onion and tomatoes, add the browned meat and bay leaves.
Simmer on low for at least one hour stirring occasionally.
If it sticks to the bottom, the heat is too high. Chop potatoes and carrots to desired sizes and add to mixture. Cut the corn on the cob pieces in half (making 1/4 size cobs) and add to mixture.
Simmer until potatoes and carrots are done.

title: tuna on a shoestring
directions: In large bowl, separate tuna chunks.
Add carrots, celery, onions and mayo.
Toss well; cover and chill for 3 hours.
Just before serving, fold in potato sticks or serve over bed of lettuce over potato sticks and garnish around the edge with tomato or avocado wedges.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bird's bread wreath
directions: Thaw dough until just soft.
Cut lengthwise into 2 strips. Roll each piece to about 18-inches.
Pinch 2 ends together and twist 2 ropes together.
Form into a wreath.
Pinch ends together. Place on cookie sheet, cover and let rise.
Brush with egg yolk and water.
Cover with bird seed and press seed into wreath.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Hang outside in tree.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cook shortening and flour on low heat in skillet, stirring constantly, until dark brown. Add salt, pepper and red pepper during browning. Add remaining ingredients and water. Cook slowly for 2 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased 9 X 13 baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Take out of oven and sprinkle 1/4 to 1/2 c. grated cheese on top and let melt.
Can be prepared at night to cook the following morning.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil for 2 minutes at full boil.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and stir.
Pour over the popcorn.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 40 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, syrup, sugar, flour, salt and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Add pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with pecan halves.
Bake at 350° at least 45 minutes or middle of pie is firm.

title: soft enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and sausage with chopped onion in a large skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste. Drain off excess grease.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Toast 1/2 c. coconut; set aside. Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; cool slightly. Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat eggs. Add condensed milk, water, vanilla, salt and nutmeg, mix well. Stir in remaining 1/2 c. coconut. Pour into prepared pastry shell. Sprinkle with toasted coconut. Bake 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool, chill if desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix ingredients together. Bake for 25 minutes at 350° in a greased pan.

title: fried potato and onion
directions: Fry potatoes in oil and butter.
Let get 1/2 way done and put in onions and green peppers.
Let get all the way done; add sugar and brown.

title: granny's corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add combined sugar and cornstarch; mix. Add milk, corn and melted margarine; mix.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt half of the butter and add to Stove Top dressing.
Use the other butter with the rest of mixture.
Mix and cook at 325° for 1 hour.
May add grated cheese, if you wish.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing but do not let stand. Spoon stuffing across center of 2-quart shallow baking dish. Arrange chicken around stuffing.
Combine soup, milk and parsley. Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir sauce before serving.

title: bird's nests
directions: Combine cereal and coconut in bowl.
Combine other ingredients in saucepot and bring to a boil while stirring.
Remove from heat. Stir in cereal mixture.
Let cool, shape into bird's nests.
Fill with "jelly bean eggs".

title: pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and 2 eggs. Add 2/3 cup juice.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake until center is set, 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: sausage roll
directions: Roll biscuit dough real thin.
Put sausage on it and roll it up.
Cut slices and place on cookie sheet.
Cut margarine in small slices and put on top of sausage rolls.
Bake until lightly brown.

title: egg casserole
directions: Layer sausage, mushrooms, cheese and onions in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix well; chill.
Serve over green tossed salad.

title: squash casserole(even kids will love it)
directions: Slice and boil squash in salted water for 10 minutes.
While that is boiling, mix all other ingredients.
Drain water. Pour mixture over squash in 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish, measuring 8 x 12-inches.
Top with remaining ingredients after they have been blended together.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs in a shallow dish or pan.
Add salt, sugar, nutmeg and milk.
Dip bread into egg mixture.
Coat on both sides.
Fry on greased griddle until toast is brown on both sides.

title: meat loaf hawaiian
directions: Drain juice from pineapple; add water to make 1 cup.
Cook the juice and water mixture, cornstarch, brown sugar and vinegar until thick.
Add the pineapple chunks and bell pepper.
Make meat loaf with remaining ingredients; bake to brown, then cover with sauce. Serve hot.

title: delicious broccoli
directions: Rinse vegetables and separate into small pieces.
Steam until desired tenderness.
Sprinkle with small amount of lemon juice. Toss with dressing to taste.
Serve immediately or chilled.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Combine refried beans, drained pinto beans, taco seasoning mix, pepper sauce and water in medium skillet.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring often.
Cool slightly.
Spread bean mixture onto large platter.
Spoon sour cream evenly over beans and sprinkle with cheese.
Garnish with tomato and avocado.
Chill 1 hour.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: pizz-a-roni
directions: Brown in skillet the ground beef, green pepper, onion and hot sausage (skin removed).
Drain and add sauce.
Cook rigatoni. Drain.
Add sauce to rigatoni and mix well.

title: quail or dove with brown rice
directions: Combine
flour,
cornmeal, salt and pepper, then pour 9 ounces of
water	over birds.
Cook until tender in a covered skillet. Add 6 cups of water to the brown rice and cook.

title: full-proof pie crust
directions: In large bowl stir together with fork flour, sugar, and salt. Cut in shortening with fork until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat together water, vinegar, and egg.
Add to flour mixture and stir until all ingredients are moistened.
Divide dough in 5 portions and with hands shape each in flat round patty ready for rolling, wrap each patty in waxed paper and chill at least 1/2 hour.
When you are ready to use the pie crust.
Lightly flour both sides of the patty and roll out on floured board.
Roll from center to 1/8 inch thickness and 2 inches larger than inverted pie pan.
Fold in halves or quarters to transfer to pie pan, unfold and fit in loosely.
Press with fingers to remove air pockets.
Fill, flute edge and bake as directed in individual recipe.
Bake on lower rack to prevent soggy bottom crust.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Put all listed ingredients into a small brown paper bag and shake.
Taste flour mixture to see if it's the right flavor for your taste.
You may want to add a little more seasoning.
Wash pieces of chicken.
Put one piece at a time into the bag, shaking off excess flour.
Put into hot oil.
Cover the skillet and turn heat down to medium.
Don't turn the chicken over until it has browned well.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix last four ingredients (except 1/3 cup of Cool Whip for topping).
Layer wafers, bananas and mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Get a box from the grocery store.
Put in eggs and milk.
Put it in the oven and cook for 8 minutes.
Then you eat them.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add chicken broth; simmer 10 minutes.
Add pureed pumpkin.
Blend at high speed until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer to blend flavors. Sprinkle with cinnamon before serving.

title: rocky strawberry smoothie
directions: Reserve 4 strawberries for garnish and cut out hull or "cap" from remaining strawberries.
Place strawberries, milk, yogurt and nuts in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed (30 seconds). Pour mixture into 4 glasses.
Garnish each glass with a strawberry.
Sprinkle a little cinnamon in froth.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in muffin pans.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: white chili
directions: In a large crock-pot, combine the drained beans, chicken, onion, pepper, jalapeno peppers, garlic, cumin, salt and oregano. Stir in chicken broth. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or high for 4 to 5 hours.

title: salmon patties
directions: Pour oil off salmon; remove bone.
Crumble 2 slices bread and one egg.
Mix with salmon until smooth.
Sift meal and flour together.
Press salmon mixture into patties, in meal mixture.
Put oil in skillet; let get hot.
Put salmon patties in; let brown, then turn until completely crispy brown.
Lay on paper towel until drained.
Serve.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into ball.
Roll cheese ball in finely chopped nuts to coat.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: honey lemon slaw
directions: In medium bowl, stir together first 6 ingredients.
Add cabbage; toss to coat well.
Cover.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into ball.
Roll the ball in the chopped nuts until well covered.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Wrap chicken breasts securely in heavy foil.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Cool and reserve broth.
Tear chicken into large bite size pieces.
Set aside.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray bottom of 3-quart microwavable dish with Pam.
Spread nuts and coconut in bottom of dish.
Mix cake mix, eggs, water and oil.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Heat cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar; pour over cake mixture.
Bake in microwave on High for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 380° for 10 minutes.
Good, if frosted also.

title: lazy day stew
directions: In large kettle, place stew meat, then soups, potatoes and then rest of veggies. Cover tightly and bake for 5 hours at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour, Karo syrup, butter and vanilla.
Pour this mixture over the pecans in the pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: icebox cookie dough
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add other ingredients; shape into rolls and chill.
Cut off rolls in size desired; place on cookie sheet and bake at 350°.
Yield varies with size cut.

title: world's best potatoes
directions: After potatoes are cool, grate them coarsely.
Mix together margarine, soup, cottage cheese and onion.
Put into flat casserole dish and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: frozen slaw
directions: Salt cabbage.
Let sit 1 hour and rinse.
Add celery and green pepper to cabbage.
Boil remaining ingredients.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage and freeze.

title: iced tea
directions: Boil and let set
for
hour water and tea bags.
Add sugar while hot.	Pour in gallon container and fill with water and ice cubes.
Enjoy!

title: quick cheesed onions
directions: Cook onions in boiling salted water until tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Drain.
Place cheese spread in double boiler. Gradually add cream and heat thoroughly.
Pour over onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Clean chicken breasts thoroughly, removing any fat.
Pound breasts to 1/2-inch thickness with kitchen mallet; set aside.
Mix eggs and water in shallow dish.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and then dredge through the bread crumbs.
Be sure to fully coat the chicken.
Coat the bottom of a frying pan with olive oil and heat pan, being careful not to overheat.
Place coated cutlets into pan and cook until thoroughly done (about 2 minutes on each side). Once thoroughly cooked, top with shredded Mozzarella cheese and cover with sauce.
Place cover on pan and heat until cheese is melted and sauce is hot.
Serve with your favorite pasta and garlic bread.

title: three milk cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar gradually.
Mix together flour and baking powder.
Add flour mixture and 1/2 cup milk alternately, by hand.
Add vanilla.
Grease an 8 x 10-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool completely before continuing!

title: nut'n to it cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in 3 layers at 325°.
When done, turn out of pan and let cool.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into 9-inch square baking pan.
Add vanilla, vinegar and shortening.
Pour water over mixture and mix thoroughly to make sure all ingredients are moistened.
A cup of chopped apples and 1/2 cup chopped nuts may be added.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and spoon into 2-quart greased casserole. Add topping and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix and serve with fruit.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet; drain.
Add taco seasoning and cook for a few minutes.
In large bowl, mix remaining ingredients, add beef.
Serve with tortilla chips, taco sauce and Ranch dressing.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Crush pretzels and add brown sugar and butter. Press into baking dish and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen vienna tortes
directions: Spread half of the quart of chocolate ice cream in each of the crusts; freeze.
Spread half of the coffee ice cream on top of the chocolate layer; freeze.
Soften the vanilla ice cream; whip cinnamon into it.
Divide and spread on each pie.
Freeze.

title: pasta rolls
directions: Remove casing from sausage.
Crumble sausage in skillet.
Brown sausage; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in 1/2 cup sauce and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover each noodle with approximately 1/3 cup sausage mixture; roll up, starting at narrow end.
Place seam side down in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over noodles; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese; cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot or microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cottage cheese dill bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water. Add egg, cottage cheese, sour cream, sugar, spices and butter. Mix well. Add dry ingredients and knead until smooth. Place in a greased bowl. Cover and let rise until double in bulk. Punch down. Place in loaf pan and let rise until doubled. Bake at 400° (until loaf sounds hollow when tapped), approximately 25 minutes.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Cut eight Asparagus spears into 4 inch pieces; cut remaining spears into 2 inch pieces.
Cook all of the asparagus in a small amount of water until tender; drain and set aside.
Line the unpricked Pastry Shell with a double thickness of heavy-duty foil. Bake at 450 for 5 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 5 minutes longer. Remove from the oven and set aside.
In a saucepan over medium heat, melt Butter; stir in Flour and Salt.
Gradually add milk; cook and stir until thickened.
Stir a small amount into eggs; return all to pan.
Stir in Cheese and 1/2 inch Asparagus pieces. Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with Bread Crumbs.
Bake at 400 for 35 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Arrange the 4 inch Asparagus pieces in a spoke pattern on top. Yield:
6 - 8 servings.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together until light and fluffy.
Add sour cream and preserves.
Sift dry ingredients into first mixture thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen large cookies.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Should set in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: citrus fruit scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift flour with sugar, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt; then sift again.
Cut butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; add citrus fruit, toss to distribute evenly, then add beaten eggs.
Mix with fork until mixture forms a ball.
Pat dough into rounds and place on greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart; brush tops with milk.
Bake 15 minutes.
Makes 15 to 18 scones.

title: raspberry angel dessert
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin in bowl.
Stir until dissolved. Tear cake into 1-inch pieces.
Separate raspberries with fork. Save a few berries for garnish; add remainder to gelatin. Refrigerate gelatin until slightly thickened (not set), 15 minutes.
Layer half of cake pieces, gelatin mixture and yogurt in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Repeat.
Garnish with reserved raspberries. Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Mix by hand Bisquick, milk and cheese.
Form biscuits and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix melted butter and garlic and brush over warm biscuits.
Similar to Red Lobster's biscuits.

title: easy chicken
directions: Cook chicken, remove from bone and cut into bite-size pieces. Saute onion in butter.
Blend in chicken soup, milk, parsley, lemon juice and sherry.
Heat slowly for 30 minutes.
Fold in chicken.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on greased pizza pan. Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: crispy cheddar crackers
directions: Spray baking sheet with nonstick coating.
Mix flour, walnuts, paprika and onion powder.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cheese.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon water over mixture.
Gently toss with a fork.
Repeat until all are moistened.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry pudding; add remaining ingredients. Don't drain pineapple.
That's it.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Layer raw chicken (boneless and skinless) on bottom of pan, then the ham and cheeses.
Spread undiluted Cheddar soup over. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato pancakes you won't believe(with applesauce)
directions: Grate potatoes.
Rinse in cold water.
Drain.
In bowl, mix potatoes, onion, garlic, egg, flour, cornstarch, white pepper and 1 1/2 cups Blue cheese.
Preheat skillet.
Coat with butter or oil. Pour mix into pan.
Pat down firmly to make one big pancake.
Fry until golden brown on one side.
Slice onto plate and invert onto another plate.
Slide back into frypan.
When browned, move onto serving plate.
Sprinkle with remaining Blue cheese.
Accompany with warm applesauce.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: turkey breast stuffed with chilies and cheese
directions: Debone breasts; cut between bone and flesh.
Pull bone away as you loosen.
Do not remove skin.
Cut meat horizontally in half. Cover with plastic wrap.
Pound with skillet to even thickness. Refrigerate until ready to stuff.
Prepare stuffing, saute green onion and sweet red pepper in 2 tablespoons of butter in medium skillet, over medium heat until tender.
Add cumin, coriander, chili powder, salt and pepper; saute 1 minute.
Add chilies; stir. Remove from heat.
Stir in crumbs, cheese and eggs.

title: dick's hot wings
directions: In a bowl combine margarine, cayenne pepper sauce, dressing mix, poultry seasoning, paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, red pepper flakes, oregano, honey, Tabasco and beer.
Set aside.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: walnut pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie shells.
Don't preheat oven.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with ice cream or top with Cool Whip.

title: bee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into dough. Spread in pan and add filling on top.

title: impossible egg custard
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour in large greased pie pan.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: greek cookies
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together flour and baking powder in a separate bowl.
Add dry mixture to liquid. Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Place batter in 2 aluminum ice cube trays or bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. After baking, cool, slice and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown (about 5 minutes on each side).

title: sweet potato-pineapple casserole
directions: Layer sliced sweet potatoes, pineapple, marshmallows, pecans and cherries in baking dish.
Cook together margarine, sugar, cornstarch, orange juice and pineapple juice until hot.
Pour over potato mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican hash
directions: This is good poured over corn chips in a baking dish and sprinkled with cheese for a crowd.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: jello knox blox
directions: In large bowl mix gelatins.
Add boiling water and stir until completely dissolved.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add soup and broccoli.
Let it cook for 5 to 10 minutes until broccoli is done, then serve.

title: a luncheon sandwich
directions: In center of plate, stack first 9 ingredients and then place sliced boiled egg around base of sandwich.
This serves one and makes a pretty luncheon plate.

title: cold corn salad
directions: Boil 30 minutes.
Put in pint jars and seal.

title: burgundy ribs
directions: Place ribs in large pot.
Add water to cover.
Add salt. Bring to boil; cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Combine all remaining ingredients in separate pan.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain ribs and place in shallow baking dish.
Brush generously with wine baste mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, brushing often.
Turn ribs.
Baste and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: hot tuna salad buns
directions: Combine ingredients except buns.
Fill buns; wrap in foil. Heat in a slow oven at 300° about 30 minutes.

title: biscotte
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add some of water, throw in whole almonds, add honey.
Stir and add rest of water.
Roll into logs; slice on bias 1/2-inch.
Place on pan, cut side down, and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
They will flatten out as they bake.

title: oatmeal rolls(yields 160)
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixer.
Mix 3 minutes.
Add shortening.
Mix 3 minutes on low speed.
Add 60° to 70° water. Mix on low until blended.
Mix on high 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Shape into rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: autumn spiced tea(mix)
directions: Mix all in a bowl, then store in airtight container (all ingredients are dry).
Use 2 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup of hot water to prepare hot tea drink.

title: chicken strata
directions: Mix bread, chicken, celery, onion, mayonnaise and grated cheese, and put into a 9x13 casserole dish. Combine eggs, milk and soup and pour over bread mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 350° for one hour, or more if needed. Sprinkle more cheese on top, and continue baking until the cheese is melted.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside overnight.
An hour before serving, add remaining ingredients.

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together with wire whip.
Add melted butter and stir well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon berries over batter; sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple-orange cooler
directions: In a 2-quart pitcher, combine the pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice and set the pitcher aside.
Fill 4 (12 ounce) glasses with ice cubes.
Divide the fruit mixture among them, then top with the seltzer water.
Stir this thoroughly to mix.
Add garnish if you like with the orange slices.

title: old-fashioned molasses cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Make a dough as making biscuits.
Roll out in thin layers and bake just enough to brown on both sides.
Have dried apples cooked and ready.
Put a layer of apples between each layer of cake.
Make it as high as desired. Let cake set for at least a day or so in refrigerator before serving.

title: lime mold
directions: Heat pineapple.
Dissolve Jell-O in it.
Stir in cream cheese which has been softened to room temperature.
Cool slightly.
Add nuts and celery.
Fold in Dream Whip.
I sometimes use Cool Whip. Chill to set.

title: meatball potato scallop
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and lightly shape into 16 balls.
Brown on all sides in hot oil in skillet.
Remove meatballs and pour off all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Add onion and saute 2 or 3 minutes.
Add soup, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Mix this with crushed graham crackers so you can mold it. Cool or freeze so it can be sliced.
Slice and top with whipped cream.

title: milk gravy
directions: After you cook your meat (bacon/sausage), use the leftover grease to make your gravy or you can just use regular cooking oil. Put enough grease to cover the bottom of the skillet.
Add about a 1/4 cup or so of flour; mix it together good.
Then add milk and water.
Add more milk and water to get it thinner or more flour if you want it thicker.
Add salt, pepper and garlic if you wish.
Not a whole lot or it will be too garlicy.
Let simmer or a while.
The longer it cooks, the thicker it will get.
Stir often.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife test comes out clean.

title: rich corn bread
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Bake in greased pan for 20 minutes in hot oven at 450°.

title: ice cream crunch
directions: Combine
dry
cake
mix,
butter
and nuts.
Spread
on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.
Remove
and
stir constantly to crumble.
Layer half the cooled crumbs in
x 13-inch pan. Slice and layer ice cream on top.
Pour
caramel topping on top and then the rest of crumb mixture.
Freeze and slice.

title: diet congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add cottage cheese, Cool Whip and lime jello.
Mix well.
Smooth out in a dish and top with red cherries. Chill and serve.

title: rocky road ice cream
directions: Dissolve sugar in cream and half and half.
Add salt and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate syrup (additional syrup can be added to make a stronger chocolate taste).
Add nuts and marshmallows. Chill for 20 minutes.

title: black forrest pie
directions: Spread 1 cup Cool Whip on crust bottom.
Combine milk and pudding on low speed 1 minute.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Spread over whipped topping in crust.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top, leaving 1-inch border and a depression in the center. Spoon cherry pie filling in center and chill 3 hours.
Garnish with chocolate.

title: gnocchi
directions: Rice potatoes and form into a ring.
Break eggs into ring. Put flour all around ring and sprinkle salt over all.
After the potatoes have cooled, gradually incorporate the flour, eggs and potatoes with your hands.
Roll between floured hands into rolls the thickness of a finger and 6 to 12 inches long.
Cut each rope into pieces about 1 inch long.
They can be frozen at this time.

title: pasta con fagioli
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Drain and place in saucepan; cover beans with	fresh
cold
water
and bring to a boil.
Add all ingredients except Pasta, cover and simmer over low heat until beans crush easily between fingers, about 2 1/2 hours. Add pasta and
simmer
until
it
is
tender, about 10 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: easy rolls *
directions: Dissolve yeast in water, add oleo, egg and sugar.
Add flour a little at a time.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes in greased muffin pans (may be greased with Pam).
Batter may be stored in sealed container in the refrigerator for several days for later use.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix according to directions.
Spread on 2 pie pans. Bake cookie crust according to temperature on box, then cool completely.
Mix 8 ounces cream cheese with sugar.
Spread on crust.
Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Spread on top of cream cheese. Slice banana on top.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saut onions in butter until tender. Add soup and sour cream and stir until mixed well. (Be sure to break hash browns up before you open the bag.) Thaw the hash browns for a

minute in the microwave so they will stir easily. In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except reserved butter and breadcrumbs. Put in well-greased casserole dish. Sprinkle top with remaining butter and top with breadcrumbs. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: friendship starter 2
directions: Drain all fruits well.
Combine all ingredients in non-melt bowl.
Stir gently.
Cover and let stand at room temperature 3 weeks.
Stir twice weekly.
Reserve at least 1 cup of this starter at all times.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Brown round steak and simmer with 4 cups water or more for at least 45 minutes.
Add salt and onion.
Add noodles and cook 10 minutes more.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with crushed potato chips.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add poppy seed filling.
Add egg yolks (one at a time), beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla and sour cream.
Sift or mix together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add gradually to poppy seed mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Fold into mixture stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: red cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and cream until well blended.
Mix food coloring and cocoa together and add to the creamed mixture.
Sift salt, soda and cake flour.
Add dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Fold, but do not beat.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour and pineapple; mix in the eggs. Trim bread; cube and toast.
Pour melted butter over cubed bread. Mix with pineapple mixture.
Spray a 1-quart casserole and fill with mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes at 425° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Cut potatoes into quarters and scoop out the potato leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Place skins in a baking pan and brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, grated cheese and paprika.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, until crisp.
Top off with bacon bits.

title: italian beef and zucchini dinner
directions: Combine garlic, basil and pepper.
Divide mixture in half. Press half of seasoning mixture evenly into both sides of beef steaks; reserve.
Heat oil and remaining seasoning in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add zucchini; cook and stir 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cook and stir 1 minute.
Remove vegetables to platter.
Sprinkle with cheese and keep warm.
Increase heat to medium-high.
Place 2 steaks in same skillet.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, turning once.
Repeat.
Season steaks with salt, if desired.
Serve with warm vegetables.
Makes 4 servings.

title: decorator cookies
directions: Blend salt and flour in bowl, adding water gradually.
Knead 7 to 10 minutes until firm.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 325° until hard.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix everything in a bowl.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: blueberry batter cake
directions: Line an 8 x 12-inch pan with blueberries. Sprinkle lemon juice over fruit. Cream together 3/4 cup sugar and butter with electric mixer. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add milk, alternating with flour mixture, to creamed sugar and butter, a little at a time, to make batter.
Pour batter over berries. Combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt. Sprinkle over batter. Pour boiling water over cake.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix pudding mix, sugar, milk and vanilla; pour in freezer can. Add strawberries.
Finish filling with homogenized milk.

title: apple diet cake
directions: You will need 8 to 10 wooden sticks.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Bake in slow (225°) oven, stirring mixture with a wooden spoon.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 9 quarts.

title: lo-cal jello salad
directions: Heat Jell-O and pineapple with juice in pan.
Bring to boil; cool.
When Jell-O is cool, mix in the Cool Whip and buttermilk. Chill in 9 x 13-inch pan until set.

title: easy beef and mushroom dish
directions: You will decide quantity according to your own needs.
As a rule, 2 cans of soup to 1 to 1 1/2 pounds beef cubes and 1 large jar sliced mushrooms.
Add ingredients to crock-pot.
If using these quantities, add small amount of water (about 1/4 of one soup can).
Slow cook in crock-pot, covered, for approximately 8 hours. Serve over rice or noodles and a vegetable of your choice. E-A-S-Y and D-E-L-I-C-I-O-U-S!

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Boil carrots only until tender.
They should be crisp.
Do not overcook.
Mix the remaining ingredients and carrots.
Let stand overnight.
They will keep a long time in the refrigerator.
Serve them cold with your meal.

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix together warm water, sugar, salt and dry yeast and stir until dissolved. Stir in beaten egg and shortening; add your flour and mix well. Set in the refrigerator until raised. Shape into rolls and set to raise at room temperature
for 1 hour, then bake for 20 minutes. Use two 9 x 13-inch pans. Serves 24.

title: lumpiang saging(banana egg roll)
directions: Separate egg roll wrappers individually.
Place a slice of banana on wrapper.
Top with shredded Langka and wrap, egg roll style.
Heat oil in deep frying pan and fry egg rolls until golden brown.
Cool and serve.

title: fresh strawberry tarts
directions: Combine beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cook pudding mix according to package directions using the egg-milk mixture as the liquid. Remove from heat.
Cut cream cheese in pieces and add to hot pudding; beat until cheese is melted.
Let mixture cool about 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Crush graham crackers; slice bananas.
Put alternate layers of bananas and graham crackers in baking dish, making four layers in all.
Beat the eggs; add sugar and beat again thoroughly.
Stir into the milk.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy corn casserole
directions: Add drained whole kernel corn and cream-style corn together. Add melted margarine to corn and mix well. Add sour cream and cornbread mix. Salt and pepper to taste. Pour into greased 10-inch square glass pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cover with foil when baking. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: melt in your mouth sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg, vanilla and lemon extract.
Blend in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: hot hamburger dip(1 quart)
directions: Saute beef until brown; add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and stir over low heat until cheese melts. Spoon into chafing dish and keep warm.
Serve with sturdy corn chips.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables.
Add to canned vegetables the pimento, chopped celery and green onions.

title: chocolate praline layer cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a small heavy saucepan, combine butter, 1/4 cup whipping cream and brown sugar.
Cook over low heat just until butter is melted, stirring occasionally.
Pour into two (8 or 9-inch) round cake pans; sprinkle evenly with chopped pecans.

title: fast 'n easy never fail pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly in 2-quart mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup, melted butter and pecans; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: sweet and pungent spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs in oil and set aside.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add onion and green pepper and saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except cornstarch and water to onion and green pepper.
Heat until bubbly.
Mix cornstarch and water together and add to sauce; cook 5 minutes.
Add ribs and simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tuna dip
directions: Gradually add salad dressing to cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Mix together the soup, water and flour until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: autumn soup
directions: Note:
1 (28 ounce) can tomatoes with liquid can be substituted for the fresh tomatoes.
Reduce water to 3 cups.

title: sand tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder in a separate bowl.
Mix eggs and vanilla in with sugar and butter.
Gradually mix in dry ingredients with an electric mixer.
Chill until firm.
Roll and use your favorite cookie cutters.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Brush cookies with egg white.
Decorate.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Great for the holidays!

title: baked vegetable casserole
directions: Fry hamburg and onion, then add cabbage and tomatoes.
Add 1 cup water, if needed.
Simmer until cabbage is soft.
Put all of this in a casserole as first layer, then add layers of beans, peas and carrots.
Top with mashed potatoes or onion rings.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes to 1/2 hour until golden brown.
Any vegetables can be used.
Sprinkle cheese on vegetables before layer of mashed potatoes.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and crumble or cut in pieces, then fry crisp and drain.
Cook ground beef and onions together and drain thoroughly.
Combine all ingredients and add about 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Bake at 350° in a casserole for 40 minutes or until done.

title: steamboat alfredo
directions: Saute seafood in butter for 3 to 6 minutes until scallops turn white.
Add sherry and simmer for about 1 minute.
Add cream and bring to a slow boil, stirring constantly.
Add egg, garlic, salt, pepper and a bit of fresh parsley.
Stir in cheese until smooth. Add cooked fettuccine and toss well.
Garnish with lemon wedges and fresh parsley.
Serves 4.

title: choco-mint burger (no-bake)
directions: Blend mocha mix into cream cheese (a bit of almond or vanilla flavoring optional).
Put coconut in Ziploc bag.
Add 1 to 3 drops of green coloring, depending on how green you want it; shake well.

title: sunny shrimp
directions: This dish is perfect for a shower as that proverbial coffee pot.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Blend sour cream and Cool Whip.
Add fruit cocktail.
Cut up bananas and add to mixture.
Sprinkle jello over top and fold in.

title: lobster roll
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and butter in top of double boiler.
Add lobster meat and mix well.
Roll out thin slices of sandwich bread with rolling pin (thin as possible).
Trim crusts off first. Spread mixture on bread slices and roll.
Refrigerate or freeze. Brush with melted butter and broil both sides.

title: marinade for chicken or pork
directions: Marinate meat for several hours before grilling.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Combine sugar and honey.
Cook to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn; stir until coated.
Double syrup mixture for a richer treat!

title: irene salad
directions: Pour hot water over cut marshmallows and jello; let stand until it thickens.
Mash cream cheese with drained pineapple and juice.
Mix together and add nuts.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.

title: broccoli raisin salad
directions: Cut up broccoli very small, even the stalks. Peel stalks and use the center, cut up. Add all other ingredients and mix together.

title: broccoli rice au gratin
directions: Grease a 2 quart dish.
Mix all ingredients in dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook in crock-pot on high for 10 hours or until thick.
Can and seal.

title: italian biscuits
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flavorings.
Add flour mixture and anise seed.
Spoon 4 long loaves on 2 greased cookie sheets (2 loaves on each sheet).
Batter will be fluffy.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Carefully lift off and place on cutting board.
Slice in 1-inch fingers.
Return to sheets and toast until golden.

title: connie mcintosh's chalupa casseroleserves 12
directions: Brown meat with onions and garlic

title: layered cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground meat with paprika and chopped onion.
Cut up cabbage into the bottom of a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with raw rice.
Combine can of mushroom soup and can of water.
Pour over rice and cabbage.
Add meat and grated cheese.
Add cans of tomato sauce and can of water.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour or longer.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, working the sausage and cheese well together. Add milk and mix well. Drop by teaspoon size balls onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400°f. 200°c. gas mark 6 until nice and brown. Good hot or cold.

title: cashew salad
directions: Mix and shake vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar, poppy seeds, dried mustard and onion salt.
Pour over lettuce.
Add cheese and cashews.
Let set into container for 2 hours (in the refrigerator) to dissolve ingredients.
Shake well before serving.
Serves 10.

title: roasted potatoes with carrots
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place potatoes, carrots and onions in a large baking dish. Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt, pepper and rosemary.
Pour a thin layer of oil over and mix. Bake in oven for about 25 to 30 minutes until potatoes are golden brown.

title: pot roast
directions: Put roast in a crock-pot. Top with soup mix. Pour in a can of Coke. Cook in the crock-pot for about 5 hours on high.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine brown sugar and butter, cook for 2 minutes.
Add milk, let stand until lukewarm, add powdered sugar and beat until smooth.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt together 8 Milky Way bars and 1 stick of oleo; set aside. Cream 1 stick of oleo and sugar; then add 4 eggs, one at a time. Then sift flour alternately with buttermilk with 1/2 teaspoon baking soda, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and add 2 teaspoons vanilla. Then fold all of these ingredients with the Milky Way mixture. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed, except omit liquid.
Add pie filling. Mix by hand and it doesn't break up the cherries.
Bake according to box directions.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Melt butter or cook bacon and saute carrot and onion until tender.
Stir in 2 tablespoons flour and blend until it bubbles, then add milk and bouillon.
Cook until slightly thickened and add 3 of the potatoes, cooked, peeled and diced.
Mash the other 3 which have been mashed.
Season with parsley, salt and seasoned salt.

title: peach delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans.

title: caddo relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to boil.
Start putting in hot jars as soon as mixture begins to boil.
Seal jars and process in hot water bath for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow fruit squares
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large saucepan over low heat, melt margarine or butter.
Add marshmallows, stirring constantly, until melted.
Remove from heat.
Quickly add cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Press into prepared pan with back of buttered spoon.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: lemon rub pie
directions: Put eggs and sugar in bowl and beat thoroughly, then add the rest of ingredients and blend well.
Bake in 9-inch unbaked pie shell at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Pie will be brown on top and when you shake gently it will shake like jello.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and dressing.
Pour over pasta, peppers and onion.
Refrigerate.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Beat together shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Add flavorings.
Grease and flour Bundt pan (or 10-inch tube pan or large loaf pan).
Pour mixture into pan.
Place in cold oven; turn heat to 350° and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes (or until cake tests done).
Let stand for 3 to 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar and salt.
With pastry blender or knives cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
In a separate bowl, beat water, vinegar and egg. Add to flour mixture, just to moisten.
Shape pastry into a ball. Place on lightly floured surface.
Cover and let set for 15 to 20 minutes.
Form dough into 4 equal balls and flatten into a disk. Wrap each one in plastic wrap, then seal in foil.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 days or freeze for longer storage.
Thaw in refrigerator before using.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add well beaten egg, milk and onion.
Drop from spoon into hot fat.
Cook until brown.
Drain on paper.

title: holiday hominy
directions: Cook hominy until dry.
Cut up cheese in Pyrex dish and pour hominy over.
Add salt, pepper and sour cream.
Spread cheese and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: super salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Add vegetables, mix in Eagle Brand milk, sugar, mayo, salt and pepper.
Chill several hours.

title: grasshopper ice cream pie
directions: Layer #1:
Crush 26 of the Oreo cookies.
Mix in butter.
Pat in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli and let cool.
Top with Velveeta cheese. Combine crackers with butter.
Top casserole and bake until cheese melts.

title: spiced peach dessert(diabetic)
directions: Drain peaches and reserve juice; set aside.
Combine cornstarch, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg in medium saucepan.
Stir in reserved peach juice until well blended.
Add peaches.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add orange extract and brown sugar substitute, mixing well.
Serve warm.
Yields 3 servings of 1/2 cup each. Each serving may be exchanged for 1 fruit.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Combine ingredients and cook slowly until tender.
If the mixture appears stringy after cooking, add a few drops of vinegar.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and milk to a boil on medium heat; boil 8 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted, then stir in marshmallow cream until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a 10 x 14 x 1-inch buttered pan. Let cool; cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: chocolate-iced squares
directions: Cook egg, margarine, sugar and cocoa together.
When smooth remove from the heat and add graham cracker crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Mix well and press into a 7 1/2 x 11-inch pan. Refrigerate.
When cool frost with icing made from the confectioners sugar, margarine, milk, salt and vanilla which you beat until smooth.
Melt the chocolate chips and spread over the icing, then chill until firm.

title: tofu salad
directions: Note:
"Some" means to suit your like.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Wash and dry chicken well on paper towels.
Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
In shallow baking pan in oven, melt the butter.
Remove from oven.
Arrange chicken in pan in single layer, skin side down.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken with tongs and bake 15 minutes longer or until brown and fork-tender.

title: fried catfish
directions: Combine eggs and milk, buttermilk and hot sauce; add 1 1/2 tablespoons seasoned salt and set aside.
Combine flour and remaining seasoned salt in a shallow dish.
Dredge each fillet in flour mixture; dip in egg mixture and dredge again in flour mixture.
Pour vegetable oil in a heavy skillet and fry fillets over medium heat 5 minutes on each side or until golden.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Blend pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.

title: broccoli and crab bisque(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan cook leeks, mushrooms, broccoli and garlic in butter or margarine until crisp-tender.
Blend in flour, thyme, 1/8 teaspoon salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Add chicken broth and cream all at once.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Add cheese. Stir until cheese is melted.
Add crab meat.
Heat through.

title: parmesan pull-apart bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush 1 tsp of the margarine over the bottom and sides of 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/4 inch nonstick loaf pan. Spoon cheese into small bowl; cut each biscuit into quarters.
One at a time, dip each biscuit quarter into remaining margarine, then into cheese, turning to lightly coat all sides and using all of the margarine and cheese.
In prepared loaf pan, layer coated biscuit quarters with edges touching; bake until loaf is browned, 30-35 minutes.
Invert loaf pan onto serving platter; let stand in pan for 1 minute.
Carefully remove pan; serve bread warm.
Makes 10 servings;
132 calories, 8g fat; 0.4g fiber.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 3/4 cup hot water over oats and let stand for 20 minutes. Cream together Crisco, brown sugar, can sugar, eggs, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and vanilla.
Add oatmeal, flour and baking soda. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: barbecue bean salad
directions: Wash kidney beans and lima beans.
Combine all vegetables and cover with vinegar, salad oil, sugar, salt and black pepper. Refrigerate overnight.
Use slotted spoon to serve.
This stays good for a week to ten days in the refrigerator.

title: enchilada bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, stirring to crumble. Crush some of the chips and put a layer in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer on all of the ground beef and onion. Top with about half of the cheese. Top with more crushed chips. Mix together the soup, enchilada sauce and the can of milk. Pour over the casserole and top with more cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 to 45 minutes).

title: company's comin' coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, first 2 sugars, oil, salt and nutmeg.
Take out 3/4 cup of mixture for topping.
To this 3/4 cup mixture, add the 2 tablespoons brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Set aside.
To first mixture, add the buttermilk, egg, baking powder and soda.
Mix until lumps are out.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with reserved topping mixture.
Press in lightly.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until done.
Keeps great!

title: lemon dill fish
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, lemon peel and dill weed until well blended. Place fish on greased grill or broiler pan.
Brush with half the sauce.
Grill 5 to 8 minutes and turn.
Brush with rest of sauce. Grill or broil another 5 to 8 minutes, until fish flakes with fork.

title: beau monde bread
directions: Stuff cheese in cuts.
Mix other ingredients together.
Spread over top. Wrap in foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger and mushroom casserole
directions: Pan-fry ground beef or venison.
Drain well when done.
Add mushroom soup and mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with chips or crackers.
Garnish with tomatoes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken; dilute each can of soup with 3/4 cup chicken broth.

Mix dressing, butter and onion in a bowl with a fork. Sprinkle layer of dressing mixture over bottom of pan, then layer of chicken, then pour mushroom soup with broth over chicken, another layer of dressing, then chicken and chicken soup with broth.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and margarine.
Spread into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix with hand mixer the powdered sugar, 3 eggs and cream cheese. Spread over cake and cover with coconut. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, no less.

title: savory sausage
directions: Brown sausage and vegetables; drain. Combine soup mix and rice in boiling water. Simmer about 20 minutes. Add sausage mixture to soup and rice mix. Add salt. Stir together. Pour into greased pan. Bake at 375°
for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls in pizza pan and line bottom and sides.
Cook sausage, then add hash browns and continue cooking until done. Spread over pizza pan.
Add cheese.
Beat eggs together with salt and pepper and pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes until done.
Be sure center is done good. Cut and serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir together and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jelly muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening. Stir in egg and milk just until ingredients are moistened.
Fill 12 greased muffin cups (or use muffin cup liners) halfway.
Put 1 teaspoon jelly in the center of each muffin.
Then top with remaining muffin mixture until cups are 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Let cool before eating, the jelly is hot.

title: jailhouse soup
directions: Break noodles into small pieces before opening package.
Use razor blade kept hidden under window sill to chop other ingredients into small pieces (be sure to have someone "jigger" for you).
Add diced ingredients into whatever container is currently available.
Fill to desired level with instant hot water from provided tap.
Allow to set for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with Doritos or crackers.

title: speedy salmon patties
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients, except butter. Mix well. Shape into 6 patties. In a skillet, melt butter. Fry patties over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes on each side.

title: baked tuna and noodles
directions: Cook celery and onion in shortening until tender.
Blend in soup and milk.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs. Pour into four 1 1/2-quart casseroles.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.
Makes 20 servings, 1 cup each.

title: mock champagne
directions: Combine the grape juice and ginger ale in a pitcher and mix well. Pour over crushed ice in tall slender glasses immediately. Makes 8 servings.

title: martha's pie crust
directions: Place the flour, salt and sugar in the bowl of a food processor.
All ingredients should be cold. Add the pieces of butter and process for approximately 10 seconds, or just until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
To mix by hand, combine the dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Using a pastry blender or two table knives, cut in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse meal.

title: grape delight salad
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and lemon juice in a double boiler. Cook until it thickens.
Let cool.
Cut up grapes, pineapple and marshmallows.
Whip 1/2 pint of cream; then mix all of this with eggs, lemon juice and sugar.
Chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple and cherries in the bottom of the cake pan.
Mix cake mix as directions read.
Pour over fruit.
Cut butter into squares and place on top of cake.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, flour, juice and rind of lemon, egg yolks and milk.
Lastly, fold in egg whites.
Butter baking dish before putting pudding in it and stand dish in a pan of hot water to bake.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together well first 10 ingredients.
Form into balls and place in casserole pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
