Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour over ice in punch bowl.
Lime sherbet may be used instead of ice.
Yield:
50 servings.

title: turkey spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix soups and water together.
Cook spaghetti noodles; drain. Put in 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Pour soup mixture over spaghetti and turkey; cover with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: roman holiday bake
directions: Brown meat; drain and set aside.
Brown sausage together with onion and oregano.
Pour off fat.
Add soups and water; mix well. Chill overnight.
Cook and cool noodles.
Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes. Top with cheese.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on flour tortillas.
Roll up tortillas and refrigerate.
Slice into pinwheels.
These are great served cold or also warmed in the microwave.

title: butter mints
directions: Sift sugar, add butter, water and oil of peppermint.
Color, if desired.
Roll in small balls and cut in pieces, or press through pastry bags with star tips.

title: greek carrots
directions: Place carrots in saucepan along with remaining ingredients. Cover.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in margarine.
Add soup, water and milk.
Mix well.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Fold in cheese last.
Place in buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and garnish as desired.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly brown.
Add 1 pound raw shrimp and call it a seafood casserole.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add remaining.
Use three 1 pound coffee cans.
Grease and flour.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours at 350° or less.

title: ham quiche
directions: Place pie crust in pie pan.
Prick bottom of crust with fork. In small bowl, lightly beat eggs and half and half.
Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle ham, green onions and cheese into pie crust. Pour egg mixture into pie crust until all filling is covered.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until the top is nicely browned and filling is set.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O and cottage cheese; add pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: steak soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Melt together flour and butter over low heat in large pan.
Add bouillon, Accent, water, Veg-All and tomatoes.
Add browned hamburger and simmer for several hours.

title: caramel dip
directions: Melt caramels.
Add cream cheese and milk to desired consistency.
Serve warm and dip your fruits.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon salt. Let stand 2 hours; drain.
Mix next 3 ingredients until sugar is dissolved and pour over vegetables.
Put in jars and put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Start eating.
Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; add taco seasoning mix.
Crumble chips into oblong pan.
Mix all other ingredients with meat.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Heat oven to 350° or microwave until cheese on top melts.

title: mushrooms with garlic butter
directions: Mince the garlic.
Wash and slice mushrooms.
Melt butter and oil in large frying pan over high heat.
When the foam subsides, add mushrooms, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are brown and tender, about 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper if needed; sprinkle with parsley. Perfect with any meat or add to pasta or other vegetables such as green beans or peas.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Set aside.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain and set aside.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dry corn bread mix with all 4 eggs.
Mix cottage cheese, broccoli, onion and melted oleo with corn bread mix.
Stir well and pour into pan that oleo was melted in.
Bake in 450° oven or 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Layer
in
large
pan
the hot sauce, uncooked noodles, sauce, Ricotta,
Mozzarella,
noodles,
sauce,
Ricotta
and Mozzarella until
all the noodles are used.
Top layer should be Mozzarella, generously sprinkled.
Sprinkle with oregano on top.
Put in refrigerator to bake later or bake immediately at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before serving. The key
to making
this, is to use lots of sauce to cook the noodles.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In medium sized mixing bowl, using fork, mix cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar and mix until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and freeze for at least 6 hours.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and onions in a glass bowl.
In a medium saucepan, combine other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers. Cool slightly.
Cover. Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Store up to a month in refrigerator.
Yields 20 servings.

title: strawberry (or raspberry) cream
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin in medium bowl; stir until dissolved.
Stir in thawed berries and the syrup.
Stir in sour cream until well blended.
Pour into 4 dessert dishes.
Chill.

title: quick mincemeat
directions: Simmer ground beef, water and salt until meat is cooked.
Then add all other ingredients and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes. Makes about 2 quarts.
Can be canned or frozen.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: asparagus and english pea casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and peas. Mix asparagus, peas and soup in a baking dish. Sprinkle cheese and cracker mix.
Top with crackers, dotted with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti and beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Combine and mix with all the other ingredients except cheese.
Place in greased 2 qt. casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until almost done or about 30 min. Sprinkle grated cheese on top, continue cooking for 5 min. more. Serves 10 to 12.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Pour into the pie crusts.
Let set up in refrigerator.

title: baked salmon in vegetable sauce
directions: Place salmon in a buttered baking pan and sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and 1 tablespoon of the butter.
Melt remaining butter in saucepan and add flour and rest of seasonings and blend.
Slowly add milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in peas and carrots and pour sauce over salmon and bake for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.

title: apricot brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan, melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and apricots.
Add salt.
Fold in flour and spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread chips as icing with spatula.

title: italian beef
directions: Place roast in crock pot and sprinkle mix on top.
Cover and cook on medium high until tender, approximately 4 - 5 hours.
A small amount of water may be added to make it juicier.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix cake.
Mix 1 egg and oil.
Mixture will be crumbly. (Reserve 1 cup.)
Press the remaining into 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy blueberry pie
directions: Put blueberries (drained if canned) in pie crust.
Mix flour, sugar and spices; sprinkle over blueberries.
Dot with butter and top with second crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes or longer until done.

title: weight watchers chocolate pie
directions: Pour milk in saucepan; add chocolate pudding and stir on medium heat.
Stir frequently.
As soon as the pudding starts boiling, remove from heat and set aside for 5 minutes.
Then stir once more and pour into your crust.
Cool in refrigerator for approximately 2 hours.
Then cover with Cool Whip and serve.

title: yummy sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut sweet potatoes in two.
Cook until tender; drain. In a medium skillet, melt margarine.
Add brown sugar.
When blended together, add sweet potatoes and simmer slowly until sugar mixture is absorbed and potatoes are brown.

title: turkey vegetable lasagne
directions: Cook pasta according to package; drain.
Lay flat on foil to cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place shrimp in bowl and crush with fork.
Add Italian dressing mix, sour cream and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Serve with chips.
Great with crackers or vegetables.

title: spinach salad and dressing
directions: Put in blender for a few seconds. Refrigerate for at least 6 hours or more.
Take out of refrigerator 30 minutes before putting on salad.

title: mother's cinnamon flops
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together.
Put in greased round 8 or 9-inch
baking pans.
Sprinkle with flour, then brown sugar and cinnamon.
With
finger,
make holes all around flop.
Dot with butter and bake in oven at 350° until lightly browned.

title: halushki
directions: Cube or dice potatoes.
Cut up cabbage.
Cook until tender. While potatoes and cabbage are cooking (last 5 minutes) saute onions in 1/3 stick butter.
As this cooks down, add another 1/3 stick.
Repeat until stick is used.

title: potato and meatball dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce and potatoes.
Make round balls.
Put potatoes, meatballs and sauce in pressure cooker or big pan with a cover.
Cook for 45 minutes or until it smells real good!

title: coke cake
directions: In large bowl sift together sugar and flour; set aside.
Mix in saucepan the margarine, oil, cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry mixture.
Then add buttermilk with soda dissolved in milk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Mix all together with spoon and not mixer.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: apple nut bars
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Melt margarine over low heat in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar. Cool slightly, then beat in egg thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Fold in flour mixture.
Stir in chopped apple and nuts, if desired.

title: buttermilk puddin' pie
directions: Combine the sugars, pudding mix, milk and butter in a saucepan and cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat, add nuts. Beat until creamy and mixture begins to hold shape.
Drop quickly in small mounds onto waxed paper from teaspoon.
Yields 18 praline patties.

title: potato salad
directions: Add 1 teaspoon mustard for color.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain most of juice from pineapple (leave some).
Place in a small casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese.
Pour on top of pineapple.
Spread crushed crackers on top of mixture.
Pour melted margarine over everything.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If serving 4 or more, recipe may be tripled, using a larger casserole dish.

title: marinated salad
directions: Cover
cabbage,
onion, green peppers and celery with 1 cup sugar
and
set
aside.
Bring remaining ingredients to a rolling boil;
pour
over
vegetables.
Pour
into
a covered container and
marinate for 24 hours.
Should be stirred once or twice. Keeps in refrigerator 4 to 6 weeks.

title: meat balls
directions: Put Ragu sauce into pot and bring to a boil.
Cut heat back. Put meatballs on broiler pan and bake in oven for 3 to 4 minutes. Turn and repeat.
Place into sauce.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice with salt until tender.
Chop bacon, fry until crisp and then put to side.
Chop celery, onion, green pepper and mushrooms to medium-small size.
Saute in butter until tender.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Put cut up rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Pour remaining ingredients over rhubarb.
Bake at 400°
for 10 minutes.
Finish at 375°
for 40 minutes.

title: spicy oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, salt, chili powder, oregano and pepper. Dip chicken pieces in milk. Coat with corn meal mixture. Place chicken, skin side up, in a large shallow baking pan. Drizzle butter over chicken.
Bake in preheated moderate oven at 375° about 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer all vegetables in a bowl.
Cover vegetables with Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle cheese over Miracle Whip.
Can sprinkle bacon bits over cheese.
Cool for 24 hours.

title: crock-pot barbecue pork
directions: Okay.
Now you put them in a pan and then you just put it in the microwave.
And then you just take them out and then you just eat them.
And if you don't want them you can save them.

title: strawberry pudding cake
directions: Break up angel food cake in chunk size pieces.
Put close together in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
In a mixing bowl, add the pudding, milk and ice cream.
Mix all of this with mixer about 2 minutes.
Pour over the cake.
Put in the icebox.
Put the Jell-O and 4 cups water in a bowl.
Let stand until thick, then fold in the strawberry slices.
Pour over the pudding mix.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to directions on package. Mix all ingredients together and microwave on High for 10 minutes. (Stir and turn after 5 minutes.)

title: chicken crescents
directions: Mix the cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter.
Add other ingredients.
Place mixture in 2 crescent rolls (still attached). Dip in melted butter and dip in crunched chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: easy smothered potatoes
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add sausage.
When onion is tender, add potatoes.
May need to add a little water so potatoes don't stick to bottom of skillet.
Cover and cook on low to medium heat. Stir frequently, adding a little water if necessary.
Add salt, black pepper and cayenne pepper to taste.
Add a dash of garlic powder.
Usually takes 30 to 35 minutes to cook.
Potatoes will turn soft and mash easily.
Serve as main dish or side dish.
Also great for breakfast served with scrambled eggs.

title: green peas nut salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
(Men love this salad.)

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Blend sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon in large saucepan; add water.
Boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter and peaches to mixture.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Combine Bisquick, sugar and cream.
Put dough mixture into 6 mounds on outside of baking dish, remaining sugar on top.
Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve plain or with cream.

title: grandma's wholesome candy
directions: Mix honey and peanut butter.
Add nonfat dry milk.
Add more milk as needed to hold shape of a ball form.
Spread on cookie sheet and refrigerate.
Cut into squares.
A snack a child can make!!

title: scotch broth
directions: Scald the barley and put in pan with meat, peas and water. Bring to a boil and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add diced vegetables except cabbage and parsley.
Season and cook slowly for 1/2 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Add cabbage and boil for 10 minutes. Add parsley and serve.

title: christmas salad(party)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; fold in strawberries.
Mix pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Add to gelatin.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream on top of chilled mixture.
Pour rest of mixture over sour cream. Chill.

title: savory lemon chicken
directions: Spray skillet with vegetable cooking spray and heat over medium-high heat 1 minute.
Cool chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Set aside.
Add soup, water, parsley, lemon juice, paprika and pepper.
Return chicken to pan.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown, crumble and drain sausage well. Grease and 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place bread in dish bottom as a liner.
Sprinkle the cheese over bread, add sausage.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour mixture over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until eggs are set.

title: chestnut dressing
directions: Boil chestnuts for 10 minutes.
While chestnuts are hot, remove shell and brown skin.
Drop again in boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain grease.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add beans, bacon, brown sugar, ketchup and molasses.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ez's slow cooker hot chili
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute the onion, green bell pepper and garlic in the oil for 5 minutes or until tender. Transfer these ingredients to a slow cooker.
Then to the slow cooker, add the ground beef, tomato-vegetable juice, soup, chili, beans, cayenne pepper, chili powder, soy sauce and water.
Cover slow cooker and cook on low setting for 2 hours.
Prep time: approx. 10 minutes.
Cook time:
approx. 2 hours.

title: bran muffins
directions: Put in large bowl.
Add wet ingredients to dry and mix thoroughly.
This will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator in a covered bowl.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight or at least 6 hours.

title: coon biscuits
directions: Melt coon cheese in double boiler.
Mix sausage with cheese. Add the biscuit mix.
Roll into about 60 small balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.
(These can be frozen.
Put on a cookie sheet. Freeze and then put into a bag to cook later.)

title: liver with onions
directions: Lightly flour the liver, then salt and pepper to taste.
Place liver in frypan over medium heat.
Brown both sides.
Do not overcook.
Serve liver that is topped with cooked onions that are sauteed in the Wesson oil.

title: baked apple casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all of the ingredients and cook, stirring occasionally, until butter melts and sugar dissolves. Pour the mixture into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Halve
each squash and hollow out the centers.
Mix the removed
squash
portions
with the hamburger, rice, tomatoes, onion,
green
pepper
and
parsley.
Mix well, then stuff the squash with the mixture.
Place 1 layer into a baking dish and pour
a portion of the sour cream, which has been diluted with the milk, over the first layer.
Make another layer of squash and pour
remaining sour cream over it.
Bake 2 hours at 300° and serve hot.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender; cut lengthwise in thick slices and arrange in baking dish.
Mix sugar and water and bring to boil.
Pour over potatoes and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, basting occasionally with syrup in dish. Top with marshmallows and serve.

title: spicy ham sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread.
Fill sandwiches.
Cut in half.
Wrap and freeze.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook broccoli.
Place broccoli, onion, soup, cheese and mushrooms in a large pan.
Heat until bubbly. Serve with large corn chips.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage, chopped onion, chopped bell pepper and garlic powder.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Simmer Ragu spaghetti sauce with meat mixture, mushrooms, salt, oregano, bay leaves, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Cook lasagna noodles; drain noodles.
Layer dish with noodles, meat and Mozzarella cheese.
Add grated Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's marshmallow treats
directions: You don't have to make marshmallow treats with just Rice Krispies.

title: shrimp betsy
directions: Heat first four ingredients together. Do not boil. Place shrimp in casserole dish. Pour sauce on top. Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°. Serve over rice or toast.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Heat butter or oil in skillet.
Add ground beef and brown lightly.
Add water, celery, onion, green pepper and salt and simmer until vegetables are just tender.
Add mushrooms, bean sprouts and soy sauce, heat through.
Thicken with cornstarch. Serve with rice.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken and set meat aside to cool.
Place all ingredients into broth.
Debone chicken and place in pot; also add noodles.
Finish cooking.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks and chunky fruit.
Reserve juice.
Mix instant pudding with fruit juices.
Add drained fruit to this mixture.
Drain cherries.
Slice cherries and bananas and add to fruit mixture.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: celery casserole
directions: Parboil celery until tender; drain. Combine with soup, milk and pecans; mix. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: canned red beets
directions: Cook red beets and put in cold water to peel.
Slice. Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat and add beets.
Heat slowly until thoroughly heated.
Put in jars and fill with liquid.
Open kettle method.
Makes 7 pints.

title: eight layer salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain and rinse with cold water. Drizzle with oil. Toss to coat. Place the lettuce in a 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl. Top with macaroni and eggs. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Layer with ham, then salami and then peas.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed and turmeric.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Pour over cucumbers.
Store in 1 gallon pickle jar in the refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely . New cucumbers may be added to mixture as long as liquid lasts.

title: poultry dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add broth until very wet.
Cook at 350° in a large 9 x 12-inch Pyrex baking dish.

title: grape-nuts bread
directions: Mix together Grape-Nuts and sour or buttermilk; let stand 1/2 hour.
Beat together sugar and egg.
Mix together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar and egg to Grape-Nuts and milk, then add flour mixture.
Add 1 tablespoon cooking oil.
Grease and flour bread pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° and test for doneness. Center will crack.
Very good when toasted.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Mix enchilada sauce and meat.
Mix soup, 1 can of water and green chilies.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil. Lay by layers the tortillas, meat sauce and cheese, etc.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: homemade "baileys"
directions: Mix and enjoy.
Makes 3/4 gallon or 3 close friends.
Good in fridge for 2 weeks.

title: healthy chicken stir-fry
directions: In skillet, saute chicken 10 to 15 minutes or until nearly done.
Reduce heat.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread; pour milk over and set aside to soak.
Add beaten eggs, the sugar and spices.
Put mixture in a baking pan, well-greased with oil.
Melt butter or oleo and pour mixture. Bake for 30 or 35 minutes at 350°.
Let come to a golden brown, but don't overcook.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Cut meat into small pieces.
Chop onion. Mix all ingredients together; shape into a ball.
Can be rolled in leftover meat or nuts.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: lemon cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs yolks.
Combine sifted flour, salt and baking powder together. Gradually add flour mixture and lemon extract alternately to butter mixture until all flour and extract is used up.
Add raisins and nuts.
Beat eggs white until stiff.	Fold into batter.
Bake in large angel food pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour and 15-30 minutes at 300°.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, chopped onion, green pepper, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with enough canned milk to hold mixture together. Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Make small meatballs and put on pan.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Put tomato sauce and cans of water in a large pot; add meat balls and bring to a boil.
Add bay leaves.
Let simmer for 3 or 4 hours. Add tomato paste and let simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: cake frosting
directions: Poke holes all through cake before frosting.
Bring oleo, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Add sugar and vanilla; pour over hot cake.

title: broccoli apple soup
directions: Peel and dice fresh broccoli stalks; peel and dice apples. Heat oil in large pot with lid.
Add broccoli, thyme, onion, apple and celery.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Add chicken stock and pepper and cook 30 minutes more.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Puree 1 cup at a time in blender or food processor.
Serve hot or chilled.
Garnish with dollop of yogurt and sprinkling of minced parsley.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Tear white meat off and layer in casserole dish.
Take can of cream of chicken soup and pour over white meat.
Take chicken broth and cook the stuffing in the broth. Then take the stuffing and put over chicken and soup.
Bake at 375° for about 1/2 hour.

title: great chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch baking dish (or pan).
Sprinkle with bacon bits; place chicken in dish. Sprinkle with Lawry's seasoning salt.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix all together, adding beaten egg whites last.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: whole wheat soft pretzels
directions: Combine 1/2 cup of each flour with the oil, yeast and apple juice in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Add the remaining flour and knead for 10 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Add more flour if too sticky.
Tear off pieces of dough, roll into long snakes and form into desired shapes.

title: pecan apple pie
directions: Core and cut up apples.
Do not peel.
Place in pan; add 3/4 cup water.
Cook until tender; add margarine, white sugar, brown sugar, sugar/cinnamon mixture and cornstarch, mixed with milk (small amount).
Cook until mixture begins to thicken. Place in pie shell in well-greased pan.
Pour pecans evenly over the pie and cook at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until crust browns evenly or pecans have browned.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Fold in Pineapple Dressing.
Fold in 1/2 pint whipped cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix butter and peanut butter, then both kinds of sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture.
Drop mix from teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: yvonne's cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions and pour in 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake according to directions on box.
Mix sugar and pineapple and bring to boil.
Pour over cooled cake.
Chill.
Mix pudding and pour over chilled pineapple.
Spread whipped topping over top.

title: beef or venison jerky
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
Use glass dishes for both marinating and cooking, no metal.
Place meat in a single layer in pan and coat each side of the meat with the following:
liquid smoke, salt to taste, Lawry's garlic and parsley mix (not too much), lemon pepper and coarse ground black pepper.
Let the meat marinate at least 4 hours, overnight if possible.
Drain off excess fluid before cooking and as it accumulates during cooking.
Cook to desired taste in low oven (250°) for about 2 to 3 hours, or until it looks and tastes done.

title: chicken salad sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put chicken breasts skin side up in lightly greased shallow baking pan.
Add water.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, dot with butter, cover with foil and bake until tender and cooked through.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Mix all together in a bowl.
Put in unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: three-cheese quiche
directions: Mix flour, salt and butter together over low heat.
Mix cheese with beaten eggs.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Bake in buttered quiche pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and brown hamburger.
Add all ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Or cook 4 to 5 hours in crock-pot on low setting.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine Jell-O, pecans and coconut. Stir into milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Chill 1 hour. Shape into strawberry shapes. Roll in red sugar. Tint sliced almonds with green food coloring and insert into tops of berries to form the leaves.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: jalapeno bean dip
directions: Grind or mash beans.
Melt butter in the top of a double boiler.
Add cheese.
After cheese has melted, add remaining ingredients.
Add juice from beans, if mixture is too thick.

title: western baked beans
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add sugar, mustard and Worcestershire; mix well, then add picante sauce and water. Cook on low for 1/2 hour.
In crock-pot, put beans and meat mixture; heat until hot.
Serve.

title: cold sesame noodles
directions: Mix together the ingredients, but use an extra large serving spoon (not a tablespoon) to measure them out.
Toss over pasta and dress with scallions.
Serve.

title: easy strawberry preserves
directions: Mix, in a gallon size or larger pan, and heat slowly until juice is extracted.
Increase heat and boil very hard for 11 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool and skim.
Seal in pint jars. Yields 1 1/2 pints.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased and floured jelly roll pan at 350° until done.
Cool before icing.

title: spicy sauce for baked ham
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; bring to boil.
Simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Add 2 teaspoons rum extract.
Pierce ham with fork. Cover with sauce.
Baste with sauce while cooking; add lemon juice and raisins to pan drippings.
Blend cornstarch and water.
Add all to sauce.
Cook until thickened.
Add rum extract and serve with ham.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in boiling water 2 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine soup, sour cream and raw carrots.
Fold in drained zucchini and onion.
Mix stuffing mixture with melted butter. Spread 1/2 stuffing mixture in 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish. Spoon vegetables on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture on top.
Add grated cheese if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
In a large saucepan, mix cubed Velveeta cheese, mushroom soup, butter and milk.
Stir over medium heat until cheese melts.
Add broccoli and sherry.
Stir until thoroughly heated and serve.
(If you are in a hurry, you can add broccoli to soup frozen, stir until heated.)

title: cranberry relish
directions: Boil cranberries, sugar and pineapple juice until cranberries pop and are tender.
Mix Jell-O and rest of ingredients.
Pour in Pam sprayed mold and let set.
Invert on plate and serve.

title: chicken-in-a-garden
directions: Combine chicken, vegetables, nuts, soup and milk.
Mix well. Add 1 cup of onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover and top with remaining onions. Bake, uncovered, for 10 more minutes.

title: power pepper dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in sealed container for 2 hours before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift flour, soda and salt into mixture.
Form small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press fork crisscross on cookies.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: special green beans
directions: Fry bacon with onion.
Melt butter.
Add Italian green beans, salt, pepper and garlic.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; dredge with flour (reserving excess flour).
Heat 3 tablespoons butter in large skillet, brown chicken and remove from skillet.
Add onions to skillet and saute.
Add wine to onions and cook over high heat until nearly evaporated.
Add reserved flour and stir to make paste.
Sprinkle with tarragon; stir in broth.
Return chicken to skillet, cover and cook until tender (about 25 minutes).
Transfer chicken to platter.
Add remaining butter and cream to skillet. Heat while stirring.
Serve this sauce over chicken.

title: peg's lasagna
directions: Brown meat, onion, garlic, bell pepper and mushrooms in 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet or pot.
Add tomato sauce and water and cook on low heat for about 20 or 30 minutes.
Cook noodles in boiling water according to package directions using 1 tablespoon oil and 1 teaspoon salt; drain.
Layer noodles, cheeses and meat sauce in lightly greased lasagna pan or roaster, repeating layers and topping with cheese.
(Have available a jar of Prego or other spaghetti sauce in event of meat sauce shortage.) Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: my often requested dinner rolls(bread machine)
directions: Place all ingredients in the bread machine in the order listed.
Select dough cycle. Grease a cookie sheet.
Divide the dough into 10 pieces and shape each in a ball.
Place 2 inches apart on the cookie sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Cover and let rise 30 to 40 minutes or until double in size.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush tops with extra melted butter when you remove them from the oven.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
In large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium-high heat.
Add pork chops; cook until browned, 8 minutes a side.
Remove to plate and keep warm.
Reduce heat to medium.
Heat remaining oil in skillet.
Add onion; cook 1 minute.
Add vinegar; cook 2 minutes, scraping up browned bits from bottom of pan.
Add potatoes and cook until browned, stirring frequently, 10 to 12 minutes.
Add apples, apple cider, ginger, cinnamon, sage and remaining salt. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until apples and potatoes are tender, 10 minutes.
Return chops to skillet and heat through, about 3 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Per serving:
524 cals.; 24 g. protein; 32 g. fat; 79 mg.
chol.; 37 g. carbs.; 339 mg. sodium.
Work time:
50 minutes.
Ready to serve in 50 minutes.

title: tasty easy chicken baked dish
directions: Mix all and top with a liberal amount of Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot cheese bacon dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese. Add the sour cream, Cheddar cheese, green chiles and Worcestershire sauce. Stir in the green onions and bacon. Put dip in a small slow cooker. Stir occasionally. Serve with crackers.

title: apple dip
directions: Dip sliced apples in orange juice to keep from darkening.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: spam casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes flat, 1/4-inch thick.
Cut up Spam in small chunks.
Place 4 tablespoons margarine in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Place a layer of potatoes, then a layer of Spam. Repeat butter, potatoes and Spam.
Top with layer of cheese.
Add seasoned salt to taste.
Pour milk over all the casserole.
Bake in covered dish at 325° until the potatoes are tender.

title: chocolate pudding and graham cracker layer dessert
directions: Make 3 layers of graham crackers and 2 layers of chocolate pudding. Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.
One graham cracker square = 1 serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and other dry ingredients.
Blend.
Add apples, nuts and raisins. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares and serve with any desired topping such as ice cream, hard sauce or whipped cream.

title: half penny snacks
directions: Beat butter and cheese in a medium size bowl.
When creamy, stir in flour, salt and onion soup mix.
Mix well and then turn out and roll into a cylinder about 9 inches long and 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill 1 hour or longer.
(Dough also may be frozen, then thaw enough to slice.)

title: mint marinated leg of lamb
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a large baking dish.
Season with generous amount of pepper.
Add lamb, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: sausage-egg bake
directions: Brown sausage 3 to 4 minutes; drain.
Beat eggs and milk; add mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix well; add cubed bread.
Fold in cooked sausage and 1 1/2 cups shredded cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Let stand in refrigerator covered overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a pie plate.
Brown beef and onions in a skillet.
Drain.
Spread in plate.
Beat milk, eggs, biscuit mix, salt and pepper for 1 minute.
Pour over ground beef and onion mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean.

title: low calorie, low sugar jello salad
directions: Mix 1 large box of sugar-free jello with 1 large container of lite Cool Whip.
Add 4 ounces of low-fat cottage cheese and 1 can drained pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: white corn salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in bowl and toss.
Combine vinegar and next 5 ingredients in a jar.
Cover and shake well. Pour over mixture; toss well.

title: suzi's stromboli
directions: Flour table and roll out dough into large circle.
Cover dough with Mozzarella cheese and top with pepperoni, overlapping pieces. Roll into loaf and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until golden brown.
Best served hot, but can be served cool.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Put chops in double boiler.
Melt chips and peanut butter. Add noodles.
Drop on waxed paper and cool.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Pat out half into flat meat loaf shape.
Sprinkle cheese and mushrooms across top.
Shape other half of meat mixture and cover cheese and mushrooms.
Seal sides and edges.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Spread ketchup last 15 minutes of baking time.

title: chicken paprikas with spaetzle
directions: Flour chicken; save rest of flour.
Cook chicken in hot oil, medium heat, until browned.
Remove chicken.
To oil in skillet, add rest of flour and onions.
Stir 2 minutes.
Add salt, paprika, pepper, water and bouillon.
Add chicken; cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: layered salad deluxe
directions: Put vegetables in a 9 x 13-inch glass container in layers. Spread mayonnaise over the top and sprinkle with sugar, salt, garlic and grated cheese.
Cover and chill for 24 hours.
Before serving, add eggs and bacon.
Do not toss.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tea-off time salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ginger, stirring well. Stir in ice tea, then pears.
Pour into a small, oiled mold and chill until firm.
Serve on a bed of lettuce. Top with mayonnaise or whipped topping.
Sprinkle with mace and garnish with a maraschino cherry.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix milk with pudding.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add to fruit.
Chill.
Two hours before serving, add sliced bananas and chopped apples.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: kass's strawberry shortcakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients with lemon rind.
Cut in shortening. (At this point, you may refrigerate for finishing at later time if desired.)

title: bisquick roll
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites and set aside.
Combine egg yolks, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Mix flour and baking powder or flour and cocoa and baking powder.
Put egg whites over egg yolks mixture.
Sift flour mixture over egg whites.
Fold under gently; don't stir.
Put mixture on cookie sheet, lined with wax paper.
Smooth even.
Bake on top shelf in oven at 350° until golden brown, about 7 minutes.

title: dungeon bars
directions: Mix butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Then stir in oats and raisins.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 1/2 hour in 350° oven.
Cool slightly and cut into 32 bars.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Alternate in casserole dish with layers of bread, sausage and cheese 2 times.
Top last layer with cheese.
Pour liquid over top and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Be sure eggs are done.

title: peach sherbet
directions: Separate eggs and let them come to room temperature.
Combine peaches and sugar.
Toss carefully to coat.
In a large bowl, combine milk, lemon juice and egg yolks; blend well.
Stir in peaches.
Beat mixture and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with foil and freeze for 2 hours or until a firm mush forms.
Turn the mixture into a large chilled bowl and break into pieces.
Beat until fluffy, but not melted.
Quickly return to original dish and freeze for 2 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in flat baking pan.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: skyline chili dip
directions: Prepare chili as directed on package.
Smooth cream cheese into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour chili over cream cheese.
Cover chili with grated Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes (until cheese is melted).
Serve with chips.

title: south of the border salad
directions: Arrange all ingredients, except chili, in salad bowl.
Chill. Heat chili; pour on top of salad.
Toss lightly to coat.

title: veggie bites
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Brush bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with about 1 tablespoon melted margarine.

title: aunt frances' ginger crinkles
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add molasses, soda, cinnamon, ginger, salt and flour.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls into sugar; flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes a large batch.

title: icebox salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour into container with seal. Refrigerate until needed.
Serve with baked corn chips.
Great with Mexican food.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add all ingredients in a large boiler.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: pound cake 3
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil and water, then Jell-O and flavoring.
Add cake mix and beat well.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan and bake in a 350° oven approximately 45 minutes.

title: russian tuna salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Put into sealable plastic bowl.
Add chopped celery, onion and pickle; mix well.
Mix mayonnaise, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic powder in a separate bowl; blend into the rice mixture.
Open and drain tuna.
Flake into rice mixture; mix thoroughly.
Open and drain peas.
Add to rice mixture; mix thoroughly.
Seal bowl; place in fridge.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.
Serve with garnish of lettuce or endive, egg and tomato slices.
Makes 6 to 8 generous servings.

title: whame cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl; set aside.
In another bowl, mix all liquid ingredients, then make a well in your dry ingredients and add 1/2 the liquid into bowl.
Stir until smooth, then add the rest of liquid and mix until smooth.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour into ungreased, unfloured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix crackers and oleo together; put part of cracker mix into bottom of casserole dish.
Add chicken soup mixture which has sour cream added to soup; top this with rest of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until very bubbly.
I have used herb Pepperidge Farm mix with oleo instead of crackers; both are good.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cream.
Stir until sugar is well dissolved; fold in whipping cream.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and freeze.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: pie crust no. 3
directions: Sift flour and salt together; cut in shortening until pieces are size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water over part of mixture.
Gently toss with fork; push to side of bowl.
Repeat until all is moistened.
Form into 2 balls.
Flatten on lightly floured surface by pressing with hand 3 times across in both directions.
Roll from center to edge until 1/8-inch thick.
Makes one 8, 9 or 10-inch double crust pie.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix buttermilk, baking soda, salt and baking powder thoroughly.
Stir in cornmeal and flour.
Add egg, cream style corn and green chilies.
Fry bacon.
Cool and crumble bacon and add to other mixture.
Pour excess drippings from skillet into mixture.
Stir well and pour into skillet.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake in the oven at 450° until brown.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour and milk, a little at a time, until thick.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Work in more flour.
Roll out and cut in shape you like.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: carrot orange mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on cold orange juice to soften.
Add softened gelatin to very hot water and stir until thoroughly dissolved. Add salt, vinegar and artificial sweetener.
Chill until thickened. Fold in carrots, pineapple and orange.
Turn into mold and chill until firm.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 7 g, protein 1 g, fat 0 g, calories 32.
One serving = 1/2 fruit exchange.

title: beef and bean soup
directions: Cut stew meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Brown meat in salad oil in a Dutch oven.
Add beef and bean seasoning mix, onions and water.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Add tomatoes and zucchini, cover and simmer 15 to 30 minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dissolve yeast and sugar in water. Sift flour and add oil to flour.
Add sugar, yeast and water to flour mixture.
Beat well 1 minute with electric mixer.
Drop into greased muffin pan.
Let rise in warm place 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: family preserves
directions: Enjoy while encouraging Godly creative uniqueness of each. Adjustments may be required to thoroughly appreciate the value of the moment.
Worth cannot be calculated.
Moments precious to sustain life will be realized through participation.

title: frozen slush
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large container. Stir and mix well.
Pour into freezer containers.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat egg.
Add balance of ingredients.
Spray pie pan with Pam. Add a little wesson oil to coat.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 500 degrees for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: picante stir-fry
directions: Prepare vegetables and chicken.
Saute garlic and ginger in oil.
Add chicken and vegetables.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Add water and cornstarch mixture.
Allow it to begin thickening.
Pour in picante sauce.

title: sissy's vegetable dip
directions: I use fat-free products to make this and it is just as good.

title: cajun chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken tenderloins into bite size pieces.
Coat with Cajun coating mix.
Heat canola oil (enough to almost cover chicken chunks).
Add nuggets to oil when oil is hot.
Brown thoroughly on both sides; check by cutting to ensure chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Serve with barbecue sauce, ketchup or any other sauce desired.

title: pork chops nicoise
directions: In hot oil in heavy skillet over fairly high heat, brown chops (a few at a time) lightly on each side.
Add tomatoes, garlic, green pepper and basil.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes, turning once.
Add olives and cook 10 minutes or until chops are tender when tested near bone with knife point.
Serve on bed of rice.

title: welsh rabbit
directions: With top chafing pan set in water jacket, melt butter.
Add cheese.
While it's melting, slowly add beer.
Add seasonings. Stir constantly with wooden spoon until mixture is blended and cheese is melted.
Serve at once on hot buttered toast.
Serves 6.

title: meatballs and cabbage(the quick way for stuffed cabbage)
directions: Drop head of cabbage in boiling water until wilted.
Remove core and chop coarsely.
Mix meat, rice, spices, ketchup and liquid.
Roll into balls and brown in oil.
Remove and saute onions.
Layer cut up cabbage, meatballs and onions, ending with cabbage.
Mix soup, sugar, raisins, salt and pepper to taste. Pour over meat.
Cook approximately 2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of two loaf pans or 9 x 13-inch or 3 small loaf pans.
Mix sugar and shortening together; stir in zucchini, water and eggs.
Mix in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, vanilla and baking powder; stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden pick comes out clean, 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix ingredients in order given (butter and sugar, eggs,
flour,
bananas, sour milk, soda and nuts).
Pour into well greased
loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese kolacky
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Sift flour with salt, sugar and baking powder.
Blend dry ingredients thoroughly with cheese mixture. Add beaten eggs.
Stir until blended.
Chill in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Pat or roll out dough on floured board to about 1/3-inch thickness.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter. Place 1/2 teaspoon of desired jam or filling in center of each round.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt oleo in skillet; add brown sugar.
Stir until dissolved. Add 1/2 cup milk; boil slowly.
In bowl, beat egg yolks, then mix 1/2 cup milk and flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add 1 more cup of milk; slowly add to sugar mixture.
Stir until thick; boil 2 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Cool.
Pour in pie shell.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Pour chili over cream cheese.
Top with thin slices of Velveeta.
Heat until melted.
Serve with plain corn or tortilla chips.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in pan.
In separate bowl, beat the eggs until light.
Add sugar and stir.
Combine chocolate mixture to sugar and egg mixture.
Add flour and remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for metal or 325° for glass pan for 25 minutes, or until toothpick is clean.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken in salted water; bone and skin.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Place broccoli in buttered casserole dish.
Place chicken on top.
Make sauce with soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour on top of boned, skinned chicken pieces.
Top with cheese and put on bread pieces, covering the entire casserole.
Spread melted butter over bread. Heat in oven until bread is completely browned.
Serve over rigatoni, rice, shells or noodles or over mashed potatoes. Serves 4.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain well and transfer to a large pot.
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well.
Simmer 1 hour on low heat.

Layer following ingredients on individual plates as follows: crushed Doritos; hot cooked rice; the meat sauce; grated Cheddar cheese; chopped onion; chopped tomatoes; chopped lettuce, and Picante sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fajitas
directions: Pound steak to tenderize.
Moisten with water.
Sprinkle with Adolph's meat tenderizer.
Jab with a fork.
Wait a few minutes then add steak to marinade, coating each side.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove steak from marinade and drain well. Grill steak over medium coals 6 to 7 minutes on each side until done.
Slice steak across the grain into thin slices.
Serve with pico de gallo, guacamole, beans, lettuce and whatever else you like.

title: refried beans
directions: In a hot skillet add bacon grease and beans.
Mash beans with a potato masher.
Add cheese.
Cook at medium heat until cheese melts.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
May use cooked green beans, red beans, limas.

title: doug's quick and easy pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon undiluted soup over chops.
Pour cooking sherry over all.
Cook for 1 hour uncovered in 375° oven or until done.
Serve with rice or noodles. Also can cook chicken the same way.

title: spaghetti a la ruff
directions: Combine ingredients in large saucepan and simmer 2 to 3 hours. Then brown 1 pound ground beef and 1 large onion.
Pour off grease.
Combine with sauce and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Layer chicken, cheese, mixture of soup plus milk and stuffing. Sprinkle butter over stuffing.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 10 minutes.
Mix other ingredients and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and baking soda.
Let cool. Cream sugar, butter, eggs and nuts. Put in date mixture.
Add vanilla and flour.
Put in layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Good served with Cool Whip or vanilla sauce.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk, mixing until well blended. Pour over butter (do not stir). Pour undrained cherries over batter; do not stir. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar. Do not stir. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Strain clams and reserve liquid.
(If less than 4 cups, add needed amount of water to equal 4 cups.)
Fry bacon; reserve 1/4 cup bacon fat.
Set aside crispy bacon.
Saute onions in reserved bacon fat for 5 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Slowly add scalded milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; then reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: caramels
directions: Bring to a boil first 5 ingredients.
Slowly add cream, without losing the boil.
Stir constantly until 240° on thermometer.
Take off of heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cut and wrap when cool.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat for 30 seconds in blender or for 5 minutes with mixer. Grease and flour a 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: red hot sauce
directions: Melt lard in skillet.
Stir flour into lard.
Add chili powder; stir.
Stir in tomato puree, water, garlic and salt.
Cook until bubbly.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Defrost broccoli in 1 cup boiling water.
While broccoli is defrosting, saute onions and celery in butter.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 soup can of milk.
After this is mixed, add Cheez Whiz.
When cheese is melted, mix broccoli, rice and sauce in casserole.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
This can be made ahead.

title: fruit plate with marshmallow sauce
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and hot water.
Heat, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Then boil without stirring to firm ball stage (244° to 248° on candy thermometer; in humid weather cook to 248°).
Beat egg whites stiff.
Slowly add hot syrup; beating at high speed until thick and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla. Gently fold in mayonnaise and orange rind.
Makes about 3 cups.
If thicker than desired, fold in 1 or 2 tablespoons more mayonnaise, or 1 or 2 teaspoons water.

title: frozen salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add other ingredients and fold in Cool Whip.
Put into 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze.

title: nut loaf bread
directions: Beat together egg and sugar and add the rest of ingredients. Let rise 20 minutes.
Bake 55 minutes in moderate oven.

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt butter; mix well with brown sugar. Add eggs and flour; mix well. Add chips and nuts. Bake in 11 x 13-inch greased dish at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Do not overcook.

title: broccoli and bean casserole
directions: Cook to separate broccoli and lima beans.
Mix together sour cream, soup, soup mix and water chestnuts and add to other mixture. Cover with buttered Rice Krispies.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ground beef dip(serve with doritos)
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add chili con carne, water and tomato paste.
Heat thoroughly.
For softer dip, use more water.
For thicker dip, use less water.

title: hobo dinner
directions: On a large sheet of aluminum foil, place 1 hamburger patty. Arrange on top onion, potato, carrot, bell pepper and salt.
Seal well in freezer for future use.
Reheat in oven as is or remove from foil and heat in microwave.
Add a pat of butter to vegetables when served.

title: seafood stuffing
directions: *Do not save with raw seafood in it.

title: little fudge cupcakes
directions: Mix together chocolate, margarine, flour and sugar.
Beat 4 eggs and add to flour mixture, stirring as little as possible. Melt chocolate; add to mixture again, stirring as little as possible.
Add nuts and vanilla in the same manner.
Fill cupcake tins with liners 3/4 full and bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: bill's fundido
directions: Wash and cut pepper, mushrooms and onion in chunky pieces. Saute them in butter until cooked, approximately 10 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Put under broiler until cheese melts and begins to brown slightly.
May be eaten alone as appetizer or as filler for tortillas.

title: oktoberfest pork chop casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole with slices of bacon.
Top bacon with the sauerkraut.
Lay pork chops on top, followed by onion.
Next, layer potato slices.
Cover with tomatoes, pepper and caraway seed. Cover and bake at 350° until done, approximately 2 hours.

title: dave's jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add applesauce and strawberries.
Stir and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Very simple but very good.

title: meat loaf
directions: Drain mushrooms. Add milk to liquid to equal 1/2 cup.
Add egg, tomato sauce, Karo and spices.
Add bread to mixture. Combine with meat and mushrooms. Spray 2-quart casserole with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: all meat seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 4 ounce empty spice container. Shake well.
It's ready to use.

title: hot dog burritosroswell, new mexico
directions: Heat tortilla over open flame.
Wrap weiner, cheese and catsup inside tortilla.

title: toll house cookie bars
directions: Mix flour, soda and baking powder.
Melt margarine, then add sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture gradually, mixing well.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut in bars.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Whisk together ingredients.
Add in 1/3 cup olive oil.
Just before serving, whisk in the juice from half a lemon or more to taste.
Combine dressing with romaine lettuce, Parmesan cheese and croutons.

title: coffee liquor
directions: Boil 1 quart water and instant coffee; let cool. Boil 1 quart water and sugar; let cool.
Mix both together, then add alcohol and vanilla. Makes approximately 3 quarts. Can be used immediately.

title: ground turkey loaf
directions: Mix all well.
Press in loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix together. Spread on greased pizza pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or browned. Let cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Warm soup; add margarine, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over hash browns, cheese and onions; mix well. Bake in large casserole at 350° for one hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: orange muffins
directions: Blend all ingredients in the blender; put into muffin tins and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Prepare Chocolate Crumb Crust.
Over low heat, melt chips, stirring constantly.
Beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Add melted chips and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into spring-form pan. Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes until center is set.
Cool; chill.

title: sliced chicken with vegetables
directions: Rinse chicken and slice them into thin pieces.
Then marinate in egg white, cornstarch, 2/3 tablespoon cooking wine, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper for 30 minutes.
Remove the stems and strings from the snow peas.
Blanch them in boiling water and drain.
Heat the wok and add 3 tablespoons of oil; stir-fry the chicken until cooked.
Remove and drain.
Reheat the remains of oil in the wok.
Fry onion until soft, then add and bring to boil. Stir in chicken and snow peas mixed well and then serve.

title: an easter brunch("cheese roll-ups")
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and egg yolks. Cream until fluffy; set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well; set aside.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Wash and hull berries.	Completely crush one layer at a time. Measure into large bowl.
Add sugar to berries and mix well. Combine 3/4 cup water and powdered pectin in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in fruit mixture.
Continue stirring 3 minutes (a few sugar crystals will remain).
Quickly ladle into sterile jars.	Cover at once with tight lids.
(No paraffin necessary.)
Set at room temperature. Takes up to 24 hours to set.
Store in freezer.
Makes 6 medium jars.

title: veggie bites
directions: Unroll crescent rolls;	place in bottom of an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch
jelly roll pan.
Pinch the edges together to seal. Brush dough with beaten
eggs.
Bake
at 315° for 11 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: twice baked potato
directions: Halve potatoes.
Scoop out pulp into bowl, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells.
Mash pulp with all other ingredients.
Stuff back into shells and bake in microwave on High for about 3 to 4 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Place croutons into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over croutons.
Let set 8 to 12 hours.
Bake at 300° until set and top is browned.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix.
Combine the rest of the cake mix, oleo and eggs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine pie mix, eggs and milk and pour over crust.
Mix reserved cake mix, oleo, sugar and cinnamon until crumbly and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top is light brown.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix vegetables and pickle in mixing bowl.
Thoroughly combine remaining ingredients to make dressing.
Pour dressing over vegetable mixture.
Mix gently.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hot rolls
directions: Put milk, sugar, salt and Crisco in pan and heat to lukewarm. Set aside.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Pat rolls into bottom of 2 (9 x 13-inch) cake pans.
Cover entire bottom.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, mayo and dressing. Spread on cooled crust.
Top with chopped veggies.
Chill.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serves 24.

title: kim's cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll in pecans.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour generously one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with the pecan pieces and coconut.
Mix the cake mix as directions on box; pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix the butter or margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour this over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Let cool; dump into another 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lettuce dressing
directions: Put cream in last.
Melt butter in pan over medium heat until light brown.
Place on stove and let come to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
Cut up lettuce and mix hard-boiled eggs in.
Put some eggs on top.

title: lemon loaf(10 slices; crunchy, lemony goodness!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a loaf pan with margarine.
Chop walnuts with food processor or nut chopper.
Set aside.
Cream 1/2 cup sugar and margarine with mixture.
Add grated lemon peel and mix until smooth.
Mix together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda and set aside.
Mix buttermilk and lemon juice and set aside.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk mixture.
Do not overmix.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into loaf pan and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and margarine.
Bring to a full boil and boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Stir well.
Have popcorn popped in advance.
Pour caramel over the corn that is in a large brown paper bag.
Shake and stir well.
Put in microwave and cook for 1 minute.
Take out and shake.
Repeat this 3 times for a total of 4 minutes in the microwave.
Pour on a cookie sheet to cool.

title: quick peach dessert
directions: Place peaches in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar, beating well.
Add self-rising flour and egg; mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon mixture over sugar and peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: thanksgiving cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/2 cups hot water. Add all other ingredients. Mix and chill until set. Best if left overnight.

title: copper carrots
directions: Slice the carrots and boil in salted water until tender.
Put in casserole with onion and green pepper.
Make marinade by adding remaining ingredients together; beat until blended.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Serve hot or cold.
This can be made several days ahead.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix ingredients in a food storage bag, kneading on the outside until the mixture resembles a very firm clay.
It should not be sticky.
Dust mold with cinnamon and firmly press in enough clay to fill the mold.
Level the back and trim the edges of extra clay. Using a sharp knife to start a corner, carefully peel out dough and place on a cookie sheet.
Using a coffee straw, poke out a small hole to hang the ornament by.
Bake them for 2 hours in a 200° oven.
After the first hour, you can place them directly on the wire racks to dry them more evenly.
When cool, tie ribbons on through the hole to hang.

title: crunch nut topping apple pie
directions: Fill bottom crust with sliced apples.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over apples.
Cover with top crust and bake in 425° oven 45 minutes or until crust is browned and apples are tender.
Remove from oven.

title: chicken divan *
directions: Line a greased casserole dish with the broccoli.
Add cooked chicken.
Make a sauce of the soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour sauce over chicken and broccoli.
Add butter, grated cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: sweet repeat
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Spread on bottom and sides of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool. Mix next 3 ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Place on top of crust.
Beat pudding mixes with milk until thick.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Add rest of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, then add all other ingredients.
Cook at low temperature about 2 hours.

title: best fudge cake with chocolate satin frosting
directions: Combine chocolate, 2/3 cup sugar, 1/2 cup milk and beaten egg in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until chocolate melts and mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Cool.

title: dre's mini burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour, until they are well mixed.
Form into tiny balls about 1/2-inch in diameter.
Flatten slightly to resemble hamburger.
Roll lightly in flour.
Fry in hot cooking oil, turning as required.
Place in hot chafing dish. Serve with barbecue sauce or sweet and sour sauce.
Eat with crackers or on toothpick.

title: irish cream
directions: Mix together in blender.
Chill or serve over ice.
Can store 1 month.

title: baked chicken pie
directions: Put the chicken, water, saffron and salt in a kettle.
Cover with the lid and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook approximately 35 minutes, until the chicken is soft.
Remove the chicken and debone.
Discard the skin and cut the meat into bite size pieces.
Strain the chicken stock.
If necessary, add water to make 2 cups of chicken stock.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Grease one 9 x 5 or 5 3/4 x 3 1/2 inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, orange juice, and pumpkin.
Beat until light.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, and pumpkin pie spice in another bowl.
Stir dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Pour into prepared loaves.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes for large loaf or 35 to 40 minutes for small loaves.

title: fried macaroni
directions: Saute over low heat in heavy skillet the macaroni, chopped onion and vegetable oil.
Stir until macaroni turns slightly yellow and add the tomato juice, salt and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to low boil.
Cover; reduce heat to lowest setting and cook for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: harvest bread
directions: Beat first 8 ingredients in order given.
Then add remaining 4 ingredients and stir until well blended.
Grease and flour two bread pans (medium) and split batter between the two pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool another 10 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: rice san luis
directions: Stir rice and sour cream together. Put half the mixture into a casserole dish. Top with diced chilis and Monteray Jack cheese. Add remaining rice and top with cheddar cheese. Bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 30 minutes.
Serves 6-8.

title: mom's yeast bread
directions: Mix yeast, hot water and 1 teaspoon sugar in bowl;
let rise. Pour
milk on top of butter in mixing bowl until butter melts. Then
pour	1
cup	cold
water on butter mixture. Add sugar and salt.
Mix	well.
Add
flour
until soupy, about 2 cups flour. Then
add
yeast
and
mix well.
Add flour until dough won't take
any
more
flour.
Knead;
let rise in warm place
until doubled.
Punch
down;
knead.
Divide
into
2 loaves.
Place in bread pans and let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: "out of this world" cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Gradually add sugar while beating. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition until fluffy.
Add crumbs alternately with milk; mix well.
Stir in coconut and walnuts.
Spoon into lightly greased 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Cook the margarine, milk and chocolate for 1 minute.
Stir while cooking.
Add the dates, raisins, nuts, peanut butter, sweetener, oatmeal and vanilla and mix together with hands.
Do not bake.
Can be frozen.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Makes around 40 cookies.

title: easy egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk and water, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: easy on the grill: ham and apples
directions: Thread chunks of fully cooked ham onto skewers with chunks of unpeeled apple.
Grill until apples are tender and ham is browned, brushing near the end of grilling time with honey or light corn syrup.
Delicious!

title: chili dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.

Transfer to a slow cooker and add other ingredients cutting cheese into thick slices and put on top, when cheese melts eat with flavored taco chips or crackers. Keep slow cooker plugged in to keep hot.

title: glaze ham sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium size bowl, combine ingredients and mix well.
Place ham, fatty side up, on rack set in shallow roasting pan in preheated oven for 1 hour.
Spoon glaze over ham and bake 1 additional hour.
Remove ham from pan.
Pour off excess fat from pan.
Pour 1 1/2
cups water into pan. Place on top of stove and boil, scraping up particles. Strain and serve in gravy boat.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt in double boiler the milk and caramels.
When melted, add pecans and mix together.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased wax paper. Melt Hershey bars and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip each piece of candy in chocolate mixture until completely covered.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Combine M&M's candies with remaining ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add applesauce.
Add pecans and dates, which have been dredged in 1/4 cup of the measured flour.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to the mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan and bake 2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: lefsa
directions: Add margarine, sugar, salt and baking powder to cooled riced boiled potatoes.
Cool completely.
Add flour and mix thoroughly. Take a small amount of mixture and roll out on lightly floured pastry cloth until thin (use only enough flour to prevent sticking).
Bake on a lefsa grill.
Brown both sides.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Boil
potatoes	(salt
to
taste) until tender, but not overcooked.
Slice potatoes in round slices.
Place a layer in a 9
x
13-inch baking dish.	Sprinkle black pepper, paprika, bell pepper, onion and 1/2 jar chopped pimentos.
Add a second layer.

title: shirley fey's turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according
to
directions,
adding 1/2 cup of mayonnaise.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan;
set other half to side.
Bake
at
350° for 18 minutes. Melt caramels and milk
together using double boiler or double pots.
Stir in pecans
to caramel mixture.
Sprinkle baked part with chocolate chips and
pour caramel mixture over that.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Return pan to oven and bake 20 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve and enjoy.

title: my cousins cheese dip
directions: Mix together (want it very moist).
Let set overnight for bacon to absorb mayonnaise.
Serve with crackers.

title: impossible pina colada pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients, except 1 cup coconut, until blended.
Pour into plate.
Sprinkle with cup of coconut.
Bake about 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chocolate "tootsie roll"
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add nonfat powdered milk. Mix well and roll on waxed paper into cylinder approximately 6 inches long.
Wrap and chill.
Cut into pieces.
Serves 1.

title: chippewa soup
directions: Mix soups.
Saute celery in some oleo, onions, carrots, bay leaf and curry
to	taste.	Blend
with
soups and add ham bone. Bring to
boiling point.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Strain in colander. Puree vegetables in blender before adding to soups. Add heavy cream.
Can
be served hot or chilled with dollop of sour cream, if desired.
Cook slow and watch it!

title: e z cheese danish
directions: Roll out 1 package of rolls on a greased cookie sheet.

title: cheddar hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes and 1/4 cup oleo.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Drizzle the 1/4 cup oleo over corn flakes.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes until it looks like it wants to bubble.

title: wayne's chili
directions: Cook ground beef until meat changes color.
Add onion.
Cook until done. Add chili powder, cumin, paprika, garlic, salt and cayenne pepper. Cook 3 minutes. Add liquid.
You may mix tomato sauce and water to make 11 1/2 quarts, if you wish.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours over low heat.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir in sugar, margarine and milk in 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Stir to full boil on medium heat.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well until blended.
Pour in greased (buttered) 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed except drain the juice from the cherries and use as part of liquid replacement for water when mixing cake.
Chop up cherries and walnuts and blend into cake mixture.
Save about 6 - 8 cherries to garnish the iced cake. Bake as directed on cake mix box depending on whether you make an oblong cake or a 2 layer cake.
Ice with a white frosting. Garnish with cherries and crushed nuts.

title: sexton paul's hobo stew
directions: Brown beef lightly; drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mock german chocolate frosting
directions: Mix milk, sweetener, margarine, egg replacer and vanilla in large saucepan.
Cook and stir constantly on medium heat approximately 15 minutes.
Add arrowroot for thickening.
Mixture should thicken and be golden in color.
Remove from heat.
Stir in coconut and pecans until cool and is of spreading consistency.

title: tex-mex rice
directions: In large saucepan, over low heat, cook rice, onion and garlic in oil until rice is lightly browned.
Stir in hot broth and picante.
Cover and simmer until all liquid is absorbed, about 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cooked rice, soup and mayonnaise. Layer rice mixture, then chicken, onion, beans, chestnuts and pimentos.
Make 2 or 3 layers. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening until fluffy.
Add egg.
Stir in flour and soda.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Fold in rhubarb.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: easy mexican soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in Dutch oven; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer on low for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: refrigerator bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix together good.
Place in refrigerator in covered container.
Wait 5 days and enjoy!

title: taco hot dish
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Add taco seasoning, enchilada seasoning, refried beans and tomato sauce; mix well.
Add and simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Top with the rest of the beans, a layer of sour cream, a layer of taco chips and finally the grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Garnish with shredded lettuce and quartered cherry tomatoes.

title: peach glaze pie
directions: Cut up 1 cup peaches; add water.
Cook 4 minutes.
Mix sugar and starch; add to fruit mixture.
Cook until thick and clear. Add butter, lemon juice and salt; cool.
Slice remaining peaches into cooled pie crust; top with fruit mixture.
Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.
Top with whipped cream and peach slice.

title: pumpkin bread or cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: smothered liver
directions: Note:
Use medium thick slices of calves liver.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Put rolls in 13 x 9-inch pan and spread dough to cover bottom well.
Brown sausage in pan so it will be crumbled and drain well. Spread meat over crust.
Add beaten eggs over meat and sprinkle cheese over eggs.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.
Let set about 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: cornbread dressing
