directions: Mix first 8 ingredients, using enough buttermilk to mix well. Pour into a greased 11 x 13 pan or two cake pans.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350 degrees.
When cool, crumble.
This can be done ahead of time and kept in refrigerator.
When ready to prepare, place bread into a large bowl; add loaf bread on top.
Beat six eggs and add.
Add black pepper and more salt if needed.
Heat broth and pour over rest.
Mix well.
A long-tined fork works well for this.
Mixture should be soupy.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 - 60 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix puddings as directed on boxes.
Layer an 8 x 10-inch glass pan with crackers, vanilla pudding, crackers and chocolate pudding until all pudding is used.
Top with sliced bananas and crushed graham crackers.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Separate rolls into individual triangles.
At wide end, place about a tablespoon of chicken and about a teaspoon of cheese. Roll up and try to close in sides so chicken and cheese will not come out.
Place in baking dish.

title: zesty glazed barbecue ribs
directions: In a large kettle or saucepot, place ribs, salt and pepper. Add water to cover.
Over high heat, bring to boiling. Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 45 minutes.
Drain, discarding liquid.

title: cream cheese muffin puffs
directions: In a small bowl combine sugar, cinnamon, and almond extract. In another small bowl combine melted butter and vanilla.
Press or roll biscuit into a 3 inch circle.
Dip cheese cube into butter mixture, and then in sugar mixture.
Place cube in middle of biscuit, fold edges over cube, sealing well.
Dip sealed biscuit in butter mixture, and then in sugar mixture.
Place seam side down in ungreased muffin pan.
Repeat with rest of cream cheese and biscuits.
Bake 12 - 18 minutes in a 375 degree oven until golden brown.
Enjoy!

title: zucchini santa fe
directions: In a large skillet, saute the zucchini and onion in oil for 3-4 minutes or until crisp tender. Add chilies, tomato, salt if desired, pepper and garlic powder. Cook and stir for 3-4 minutes. Spoon into a serving bowl and sprinkle with cheese. This has 5 grams carbohydrate.

title: slimer
directions: Safety Precautions:
Wash hands after making.
Do not ingest. Slime will stain.
Wash up quickly after a spill.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix flour, sugar,
pineapple
juice, egg and vinegar in saucepan.
Stir over
medium heat until very thick.
Refrigerate until completely cool.
As	you slice apples, combine with sauce and coat all
apples.
Fold
in pineapple, Cool Whip and half of peanuts.
Mix thoroughly; pour into bowl.
Put remaining peanuts on top.
Refrigerate.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out flat on a long baking sheet (like a pizza crust).
Bake as directed.
Mix together dressing mix, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Chop up veggies, any of your choice, and spread over pizza.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve.
Great for a cookout or gathering.

title: turkey parmesan casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup of the Parmesan cheese in large bowl. Spoon into 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Makes 6 servings.

title: children's favorite coleslaw
directions: Soak raisins in 1/4 cup water for about 10 minutes.
Drain raisins.
Add cabbage, apples and walnuts.
Spoon in 3 to 4 tablespoons mayonnaise and mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Adjust the amount of mayonnaise as needed.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pour over popped popcorn.
Place in microwave.
Set for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Shake and cook 1 1/2 minutes longer on High. Shake and cool.
Eat!

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Blend well. Better if refrigerated overnight before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, oil and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Fold in the sifted dry ingredients along with the oats and coconut. Drop by teaspoons and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. They will rise, but when they fall are flat looking, they are ready to take up.

title: lakeville, ct apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift 2 tablespoons flour, 3/4 cup sugar, 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon and salt.
Stir in egg, vanilla and sour cream.
Fold in apples and spoon into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: raisin bran roll
directions: Mix peanut butter and butter.
Add to Raisin Nut Bran.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with milk chocolate chips and butter or Crisco.

title: spiced pineapple punch
directions: Simmer first four ingredients about 30 minutes.
Strain and add to fruit juice.
Chill.
Pour over ice or frozen pineapple juice cubes.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: carolina pineapple cake
directions: Cook according to directions on box.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Blend flour and 1 cup milk to make a paste.
Stir in chicken broth.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mayonnaise, lemon and curry powder. Set aside. Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain well.
Put broccoli in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add chicken, then sauce.
Crumble Fritos on top. Put pats of butter over Fritos.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: melon ball
directions: Mix in glass over ice.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Melt butter.
Mix with cookies.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save some crumbs for top of dessert.
Beat pudding with milk.
Mix whipped cream or Cool Whip with pudding.
Add ice cream.
Mix all together.
Add a few drops of green food coloring, if desired.
Pour over cookie layer.
Freeze.
Let soften slightly before serving.
Keeps well in freezer.

title: peanut butter milkshake
directions: In mixing bowl, blend together ice cream, peanut butter and vanilla; gradually add milk.
Serve immediately.

title: butter cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar until smooth.
Add flour and vanilla. Mix well.
Roll dough onto plastic wrap and freeze.
Cut dough in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes (until edges are golden brown).
Makes 200.

title: breakfast puffs
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for abut 25 minutes. While puffs are baking, mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Remove puffs from muffin pan and roll in 1/2 cup melted oleo, then roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.

title: fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken pieces in milk and then in Bisquick.
Place in lightly coated (with oil) pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until nice and golden brown.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Beat eggs with rotary beater until fluffy.
Stir in milk, potatoes, Bisquick and salt.
Melt shortening in large skillet. Drop dough by tablespoonfuls into hot skillet.
Cook about 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Yields approximately 18 pancakes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together the sugar and corn oil.
Mix dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add eggs and vanilla; fold in nuts and apples.
Pour in greased tube pans. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: frosty ambrosia pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, milk, food coloring, orange and coconut in electric blender container.
Cover and blend at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Fold into whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 5 minutes before cutting, if necessary, for creamier texture.
Garnish with orange slices.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Drain well.
Add enough barbecue sauce to moisten meat.
Mold biscuits into muffin tins.
Fill each biscuit cup with meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Add cheese to top of each cup of meat.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Combine ingredients and let stand overnight.
Heat, strain and serve hot.

title: red bliss potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Add other ingredients. Chill.
When cold, ready to eat.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Heat apple juice with small amount of red hots until candies dissolve.
Add red hots until you get the flavor that you want.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix together; form loaf.
Mix with 1/2 can water, Campbell's golden mushroom soup.
Pour over loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with noodles.
I like to put 2 cans of soup over the loaf for the top of needles.

title: devil dogs ii
directions: Sift dry ingredients and remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Cook onion and garlic in olive oil until tender, about 6 minutes.
Add broth.
Stir in tortellini.
Simmer, uncovered, about 15 minutes.
Stir in stewed tomatoes and picante sauce.
Add green pepper.
Continue to cook 3 to 4 minutes or until tortellini is tender.
Ladle into soup bowls and sprinkle with cheese. Serves 8.

title: mom otto's famous coating mix
directions: Beat egg slightly and add milk.
Dip fish in this first, then in dry ingredients.
Pour a small amount of oil in a Teflon frypan and heat to 350°.
Turn over and fry on other side.
You can also bake them in the oven or microwave.
I also use this recipe for pork chops or chicken.
I bake chicken at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Turn pieces over and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: divine amore chicken
directions: Whip cream to very soft consistency.
Fold in worcestershire sauce and chutney.	Pour one half sauce in large oval baking dish. Arrange chicken on top and then pour remaining sauce over chicken. Bake at 325-350° for about 30 minutes.
Do not overfill.
Sauce will puff up and brown nicely, then deflate.

title: skillet brownies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Fold in applesauce, egg and vanilla.
Spray skillet with butter or oil.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mulled cider
directions: Boil together the cider and spices for three minutes.
Add carefully the well beaten eggs, beating while adding.
Strain and serve very hot.

title: buggelach
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Add softened ice cream.
Work mixture with hands.
Add flour, if needed, to make dough easy to handle. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: jelly roll
directions: Combine baking powder, salt and eggs.
Beat with electric mixer.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Add pecan halves and pour into pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven, 350° to 375°, for 50 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: chocolate mint fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine milk and peppermint and pour over sugar mixture.
Lay a whole stick of butter in the middle of sugar mixture.
Microwave on full power for 2 minutes.
Remove pan and stir ingredients.
Stir in nuts and press fudge evenly into the pan.
Chill for 1 hour, then cut into pieces when fudge is hard.

title: chili
directions: Mix ingredients, except beans; simmer about 1/2 hour.
Add the beans.

title: walnut bars
directions: Cut the first 3 ingredients to a crumble mixture; spread firmly in an 11 x 14-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Mix the remaining ingredients together; pour over the warm mixture in pan.
Return to a 300° oven for 30 minutes.
When cool, top with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti and drain.
Boil chicken and debone.
Saute bell pepper, onion and mushrooms in butter.
Put in Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cube Velveeta Mexican cheese and put on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Place half on bottom of pan, 8 x 12-inches.
Over low heat, melt marshmallows in milk.
Cool. After cool add whipped cream.
Put 1/2 cream mixture on crust. Chill.
Add blueberry pie filling.
Spread evenly.
Add rest of cream mixture.
Top lightly with crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: pepper steak royal
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Pound into steak with meat hammer or edge of heavy saucer.
Brown steak on both sides in shortening. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook over low heat for 45 minutes, or until steak is tender, stirring often.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Cool first 6 ingredients until thick.
Cool; add butter and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Make meringue and put on top.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add flour, nuts and cocoa.
Bake in an 8-inch greased pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: favorite banana-nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cream mixture.
Add banana and nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage-venison casserole
directions: Slice sausage
into
patties, cook until done, then cut each patty
into
fourths.
Drain fat, reserving 2 tablespoons fat. Brown venison in 1 tablespoon;
cook onion and garlic in remaining 1
tablespoon.
Add
green peppers and cook 1 minute until all are
tender.
Turn
sausage, venison, onion, garlic and peppers into casserole.
Add potatoes and beans, sprinkle with seasonings and mix lightly.
Add bouillon; cover and bake in 350° oven 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until beef and potatoes are tender.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Pour batter into greased pan.
Put cut rhubarb over batter. Dot with margarine and sprinkle with sugar.
Pour hot water over all.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake mix according to package in large 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch cookie sheet with sides.
Cool.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Fritos and cheese.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with Fritos and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rice-cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice and add 1 teaspoon salt.
Saute onion and pepper in 1/2 stick margarine.
Layer 1/2 rice, 1/2 ingredients, 1/2 cheese and repeat layers.
Pour half and half over it.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: china girl tea
directions: Mix tea and ginger ale.
Pour over ice in glass.

title: luscious lemon poke cake
directions: Place cake layers, top side up, in 2 clean 9-inch round cake pans.
Pierce cake with large fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in medium bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved. Pour 1/2 of the gelatin over 1 cake layer and remaining 1/2 over the second cake layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Dip cake in pan of warm water and unmold onto serving plate.
Spread frosting.
Unmold second layer and place on first layer. Frost top and sides of cake.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 12 servings.

title: salsa
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Chill for at least a half an hour. Serve with chips or great on top of burgers or roast beef.

title: silver cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine buttermilk and vanilla.
Add dry mixture to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating constantly after each addition.
Fold in egg whites.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, salt and melted butter.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch pan or pie pan.
Peel and slice apples; put on top of crust.
Sprinkle apples with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Mix in blender.
Pour over cooked carrots, onions and bell pepper that have been layered in a bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, using all or some of the pineapple juice. Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: cheese dip with meat
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Mix hamburger meat with the cheese and salsa.
Cook in the microwave for 2 minutes.

title: three seafood bake
directions: Melt oleo.
Saute bell pepper, onion and celery until barely tender.
Add a can of cream of mushroom soup or can of cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add salt, pepper, Greek seasoning, seasoned salt and pepper.
Mix well and stir in meats. Butter oblong pan and pour in cooked rice; add meat mixture on top.
Mix the rice and meat mixture well.
Top with buttered crumbs or cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice.
Make white sauce of butter, flour, salt, and milk.
Remove from heat when thickened and add grated cheese.
Place sliced potatoes in casserole.
Cover with sauce. Bake uncovered at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple and jello to boil and cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip; mix and refrigerate well.

title: donut
directions: Scald milk and shortening.
Beat eggs; add sugar and potatoes, then add milk and shortening.
Let cool.
Add yeast, then flour, knead and roll.

title: eggless ice cream
directions: Heat evaporated milk enough to melt sugar and salt.
Cool
and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer and fill with whole milk to fill line on freezer container.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Ginger is purported to be great for a cold; so is fennel.

title: good lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch dish for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine hot water, salt, shortening and sugar in large bowl. Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, softened in lukewarm water.
Add egg and half of flour; beat well.
Stir in remaining flour to make easily handled dough.
Brush top of dough with salad oil.
Cover; store in refrigerator.

title: delicious french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well.*
Better if allowed to stand for 8 to 10 hours.
Shake or stir, chill and serve on your favorite salad.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough in a cookie sheet as directed on package. Let cool.
Spread Cool Whip onto cookie dough.
Add strawberries, apples, bananas, pears and grapes on top of Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated until time to serve.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in small amount of water (1/2 cup) and let sit. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening and mix thoroughly.
Stir in buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Use as needed.

title: nut cracker sweets
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in brown sugar.
Arrange crackers on a cookie sheet.
Spoon brown sugar mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over the top.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes, until sugar is bubbly.
Remove from oven; sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
After melted, spread around.
Makes approximately 48.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add bananas.
Sift in flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir in nuts. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pignoli cookies
directions: Mush together the first 4 ingredients.
Set aside the additional beaten egg white and pine nuts.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add crumbled bread, browned sausage, cheese, milk and dry mustard.
Mix together.
Pour into ungreased glass baking dish (approximately 8 x 8-inch square or small rectangular casserole dish). Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes, no longer.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dry cereal and nut mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt margarine in a large baking pan in oven.
Remove pan from oven; stir in nuts and cereals.
Mix well. Sprinkle with seasonings; stir well.
Bake uncovered in oven 20 to 30 minutes or until light colored cereals begin to brown.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled.
Store cooled cereal snack in tightly closed containers.
If snack needs recrisping, reheat in 250° oven for a few minutes.
Makes 9 servings, 1/3 cup each equals approximately 67 calories (6 g carbohydrates, 2 g protein and 15 g fat).

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add all remaining ingredients. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger rolls.
Serves 8.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese well.
Add sugar; beat well. Then add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add vanilla, salt and flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: ione's boiled salad dressing
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs (slightly beaten), butter, milk and diluted vinegar, the latter very slowly while beating constantly.
Cook in double boiler until thick, then cool.
Can thin with cream.
Use this in your potato salad.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar till stiff but not dry. Gradually beat in 1/2 c. sugar.
Beat egg yolks till thick and lemon color.
Sift remaining 1/2 c. sugar with flour, cocoa and salt two times; fold into yolk till blended, add vanilla. Carefully fold yolk mixture into beaten egg whites.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in large bowl. Mix dressing ingredients a couple of hours before or overnight. Toss well before serving.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook bow tie pasta as directed on package, then rinse with cold water.
While pasta is cooking, coarsely chop green pepper and onion.
Cut mushrooms into quarters and cube Mozzarella cheese into small chunks.
In large mixing bowl, add cooked pasta, drained black olives, pepperoni, cheese and cut up vegetables.
Pour vinaigrette dressing over salad and toss lightly.
Refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Pour into a pie crust. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean in center (about 25 minutes). The outer rim may be a little soft. That is okay. Chill and slice.

title: wassail
directions: In a large saucepan, heat sugar, spices, sherry and ale.
If desired, add cognac just before removing from heat.
Pour over crab apples in serving bowl.
Makes ten 1/2 cup servings.

title: easy vegetable pizza
directions: Spread dip on cooled and baked pizza crust. Add Cheddar cheese. Top with cauliflower, broccoli and peppers. May eat cold or you may bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: white chocolate texas sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, white chocolate, shortening and water to a boil.
Add sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt, buttermilk, eggs,
soda and vanilla.
Mix and pour into a jellyroll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in water and 2 tsp. salt until tender. When cool enough, bone the chicken and cut into bite size pieces, set aside. Bring broth to a boil, add pepper. Combine flour, soda, and 1/2 tsp. salt. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal. Add buttermilk, stirring with a fork until dry ingredients are moist. Turn dough out on to a well floured surface, and knead lightly 4 or 5 times. Pat dough to 1/2 inch thickness. Pinch off dough in 1 1/2 inch pieces and drop into boiling broth. Reduce heat to low setting and simmer about 8 to 10 minutes or until desired consistency, stirring occasionally. Stir in chicken.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted flour, soda, baking powder and salt alternately with buttermilk.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° to 375°.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring water and oleo to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, using mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool completely.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Preparation Time: 15 minutes: Cook Time:
20 minutes.

title: tomato topped meat loaf
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in margarine 2 to 3 minutes.
Soak toast in milk until softened.
Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Shape in loaf in roasting pan; bake 375° for 1 hour, let stand for 10 minutes.
Place on serving platter and pour topping over loaf.

title: sauce for bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and milk. Blend well. Cook on low heat until boils. Blend cornstarch and water together until smooth. Stir into hot mixture. Cook; stir constantly until thick. Pour over bread pudding.

title: creme de menthe dessert
directions: Crush chocolate wafers; reserve 1/4 of it for the top.
Add melted butter to remainder and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt marshmallows in hot milk in top of double boiler.
Cool.
Whip cream; add creme de menthe.
Fold mixture into other mixture and pour over pressed crumbs.
Add remainder of crumbs to top.
Keep in fridge or freezer.

title: maryann's chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat until gray.
In another pan saute onions and garlic.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook for thirty (30) minutes.
Then add cheesecloth bag of ingredients.

title: disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch baking pan.
Mix together the cocoa and sugar; then stir in the melted butter.
Add the eggs and vanilla; stir again.
Now add the flour, salt, walnuts, chocolate bits and raisins.
Mix just until smooth, not too much.
Scrape the mixture into the pan and spread evenly. Bake at 350° just until the brownies begin to pull away from the sides, or a toothpick comes out clean (40 to 50 minutes).
Let cool before cutting.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with rhubarb & sugar.
Slowly pour cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly beat eggs in a large bowl; add sugar, syrup, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Blend well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Allow to cool. Serve with whipped topping or whipped cream.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Repeat for celery.
Heat broth.
Combine all other ingredients, then add broth and mix well.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan; cook to a full rolling boil.
Add soda; remove from heat.
Pour over popped corn; stir until all corn is well coated.
Shape mixture into balls, if desired.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight to blend flavors.

title: nutty white fudge
directions: In mixing bowl beat cream cheese and milk until smooth. Gradually add sugar.
Beat in melted chocolate.
Add vanilla and salt and mix well.
Stir in walnuts. spread into a greased 8 inch square pan.
Chill 4-5 hours before cutting.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 pound.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In large saucepot, cook 1 chicken, giblets, 4 teaspoons salt and water to cover chicken over high heat.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and cool.
Remove bones and skin.
Cut meat and giblets into bite size pieces.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix sugar and melted margarine; add vanilla and Milnot.
Boil for 1 minute.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir together the sugar, corn syrup and water in a heavy large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until temperature on candy thermometer reaches 280°.
Stir in the peanuts (try to remove as many loose hulls as possible first). Cook slowly, without stirring, until temperature reaches 300°. Remove from heat and quickly stir in soda.
Pour immediately onto two greased cookie sheets.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, jello and cornstarch and add water.
Bring to a boil.
Boil slowly 10 minutes, then cool completely.
Put sliced berries in cooled crust.
Pour jello mixture over berries. Put in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 small pies or 1 large deep dish pie.

title: sweet-sour spareribs
directions: Spread ribs, meaty side up, in single layer in a large shallow pan.
Brown in 425° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain off fat. Combine all remaining ingredients except salt and pepper.
In a saucepan, stir smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thick and glossy, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over browned ribs; spoon sweet-sour sauce over each piece, using about half the sauce.
Reduce oven heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes.
Turn ribs, cover with remaining sauce and bake for 30 minutes more or until well done.
Serves 4 as a main dish.

title: old fashioned potato soup
directions: Cook all ingredients over medium flame until potatoes appear done and mash easy with a fork when tested.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: okra fritters
directions: Mix meal, flour, onion, egg and milk.
Pour over sliced okra. Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: sugar cookie roll-out dough
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Mix in egg and flavoring.
Stir dry ingredients together; blend into sugar and oleo mixture. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Roll out dough to 3/16-inch thickness. Cut any shape desired.
Place on lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes until lightly brown.
Decorate with frosting.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Combine corned beef and chopped onion.
In separate bowl, combine mushroom soup, mayonnaise and mustard.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, beginning with cooked noodles, sauerkraut, corned beef and onion mixture and the mushroom soup, mayonnaise and mustard mixture.
Top with Swiss cheese and bread crumbs.
Spread butter pats over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt white chocolate; reserve a little to drizzle on the top. Add the chocolate chips to the white chocolate; stir until melted. Add mixture to the Rice Krispies.
You may use a little more than 1 cup.
Add nuts and finally, the marshmallows so they won't melt too much.
Spread in pizza pan.
Top with cherry halves and coconut.
Drizzle remaining white chocolate over top of all.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Pour half of the cake mix into a bowl.
Add shortening, water and eggs.
Blend well, then add the rest of the cake mix.
Beat again until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Beat all together and pour over peaches in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix flour, cocoa and sugar.
Mix all ingredients and pour in a 9-inch pie crust (uncooked).
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to directions; drain.
In large bowl, combine macaroni and remaining ingredients; toss to mix. Cover; chill thoroughly.
Toss gently before serving.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: parmesan baked potatoes
directions: Prepare grill to produce hot coals.
Rub potatoes with shortening.
Loosely wrap each potato in aluminum foil, fold edges to seal.
Place on grill and bake for about 1 hour or until tender, turning several times.
Loosen foil.
Cut a slit in top of each potato, checking for doneness.
Place 1 tablespoon margarine, salt, paprika and 1 tablespoon cheese in slit.
Yields 4 servings.

title: "good" stew
directions: Combine everything in a large baking dish.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake in oven at 250° from 5 to 7 hours.

title: microwavable mexican chili corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Cover tightly and microwave on High until hot, 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir.

title: sugar-crusted maple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Using solid shortening, grease and flour 12-cup fluted tube pan (nonstick finish too).
In large bowl blend cake mix, water and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
In small saucepan, heat sugar and syrup until mixture boils and sugar is melted.
Pour over hot cake.
Cool upright in pan 15 minutes.
Turn onto serving plate. Serve warm or cool.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup
and
boiling	water together well and cook until mixture
spins
a
thread
when
poured
from spoon (293°). Add
peanuts
and
stir
continuously,
cooking until syrup turns light brown in color and peanuts are done.	Remove from heat.
Add soda, salt, butter and vanilla;
beat rapidly and thoroughly. Pour
into	a
buttered cookie sheet.
Spread thin as possible. Cool completely and break into pieces.

title: crabmeat spread #2
directions: Mix well.
Serve with chips and/or crackers.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, ground pork, bread crumbs, parsley, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, Worcestershire sauce, egg, milk and onions. Mix well and make into small balls. Brown in oil. Remove meatballs from oil. Stir into fat the flour, paprika, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Stir in boiling water and sour cream gradually. Put meatballs back in sauce, heat and serve.

title: cranberry hot drink
directions: Mix all together on top of stove.
Serve warm on a cold winter night.

title: cheese ball
directions: Reserve at
least
1/2 cup pecans to roll ball in.
Mix all ingredients together. Chill slightly.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: velvety custard pie
directions: Pie shell should be 1/8-inch thickness.
Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
Pour at once into unbaked pie shell (fill in oven to avoid spills).
Top with dash of nutmeg.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Serve cool or chilled.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Combine in saucepan the sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in 3 cups milk.
Gradually stir in 4 slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and comes to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and beat in 2/3 cup peanut butter.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Cover with waxed paper; cool in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Skin chicken;
boil
for
5 minutes.
Drain chicken and salt and
pepper
to taste.
Place chicken on grill.
Grill on both sides
until
tender.
In microwave or top of stove, melt margarine, lemon
juice and garlic.
Mix together well.
Brush on one side
of
chicken and grill for about 1 minute or until brown; turn over chicken, brush with mix and do the same.

title: almond rice
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add rice and brown.
Add mushrooms, onions and pepper.
Saute until onion is tender. Remove from heat.
Add consomme, almonds, poppy seed and salt. Mix well.
Spoon into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Saute onion in a small amount of oil.
Remove onion from pan. Brown beef and pork.
Drain off fat.
Add all ingredients except peas and potatoes.
Simmer for 45 minutes; then add potatoes. Simmer for another 30 minutes and add peas.
Simmer for another 15 minutes.
Total cooking time is 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until soft.
Cut a slice lengthwise across top of each potato.
Scoop out middle with a spoon.
Heat butter with milk, salt and pepper.
Beat into potatoes until fluffy.
Heap hot potato into shells.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large baking pan arrange the chicken pieces.
Season chicken and turn each piece.
Arrange the vegetables over the chicken and season both at the same time. Cover the baking pan tightly with aluminum foil and place in the oven.
Let the chicken cook 30 to 40 minutes then turn each piece. Cook another 30 to 40 minutes on other side.
Remove chicken from oven and pour the juice into a pot.
While preparing the gravy remove foil from the baking pan and brown chicken on both sides.

title: hot rolls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add boiling water and let cool. When cool, add yeast that has been dissolved in lukewarm water. Add stiffly beaten eggs.
Add flour and salt.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Keep in fridge until ready to cook.

title: freeze strawberry jam
directions: In a food processor, process berries, a portion
at a time, until smooth.
Put strawberries in a 2-quart kettle, stirring vigorously.
Sift in powdered pectin slowly.
Let stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour in corn syrup and mix well. Gradually stir in sugar and heat to 100°, lukewarm, no hotter. When sugar is thoroughly dissolved, stir in lemon juice.
Ladle jam into jars; cover and then place in freezer for 24 hours.
If you want to keep longer than one month, keep in freezer. Otherwise, store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 pints.

title: week night beef stew
directions: Place beef pieces and cooking liquid, potatoes, water, oregano and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover tightly and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Add peas.
Combine lemon juice and cornstarch; stir into beef mixture.
Bring to a boil; cook for 1 minute.
Serves 4.

title: watergate cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage meat; drain.
Cut up cheese into a slow cooker.
Add tomatoes, ground beef, sausage meat and chili powder.
Let cool slowly until cheese melts and stir until mixed well.
Can be served with nachos or large corn chips.

title: mrs. myers' favorite hot dish
directions: Brown meat and add tomato soup, water and kidney beans.
Add celery, onions and green pepper.
Add sauces.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes a very large casserole.

title: ho bo bread
directions: Pour water over raisins; add soda and let stand overnight. In the morning, add sugars, oil, flour and salt to raisin mixture and mix well.
Grease 3 (1 pound) coffee cans; fill half full and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: ann's clam chowder
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Add clams and potatoes.
Cook until tender (15 minutes).
Add milk, butter, parsley, salt and pepper. Do not boil.
Do not freeze.
Servings:

title: baked yellow squash
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam. Place a layer of sliced squash in bottom of baking dish. Add layer of tomatoes, salt, pepper, layer of onions and layer of cheese. Repeat with 2 additional layers. Cover lightly with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Remove foil and continue cooking for 10 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Combine juices and tea.
Make syrup by bring to boil sugar and water.
Boil until sugar dissolves.
Add syrup to juices.
Chill before serving.
Amount:
Makes about 40 servings (2 gallons).

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix and make yellow cake mix as per instructions on box. Cook in two round cake pans.
Crumble 1 cake and put it in the bottom of punch bowl.
Make vanilla pudding and put 1/2 of it on top of crumbled cake.
Put 1/2 of crushed
pineapple with juice on top of pudding.
Add 1/2 of the cherry pie filling on top of pineapple.
Start over with next cake crumbled on top of pineapple, and repeat steps as before layering the rest of the ingredients.
Top with cool whip.

title: tuna noodle salad(low-fat)
directions: Boil noodles; drain and set aside.
Chop apples, green onion blades and eggs.
Mix with tuna and mayonnaise.
Add noodles last. English peas and pimento are optional.
Best chilled overnight. Makes about 8 cups.
Good for dieters, low-fat and high in protein.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Toast almonds and sugar over low heat until sugar is melted and almonds are coated.
Tear lettuce and romaine into bite size pieces.
Place greens in plastic bag; add celery and onions. Fasten bag securely and refrigerate.

title: sherry cherry mold
directions: Prepare black cherry Jell-O, using sherry as part of the liquid.
Chill until partially set and fold in cherries and almonds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and top with sour cream and crunchy almonds.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pineapple and pudding mix.
(I add about 2 tablespoons juice to cut the sweetness.)
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and cook in loaf pan at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crusts and keep refrigerated.
Makes 2 pies.

title: rich brownie cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° and grease and flour round pan, 8 x 1 1/2-inches.
Mix all ingredients, except whipping cream and shaved chocolate.
Spread in pan.
Bake until crust appears dry, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool cake completely.
Top with sweetened whipped cream and shaved chocolate.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Fill a large Pyrex dish 1/2 full of shredded lettuce (slice like cabbage).
Add in layers celery, green pepper and onion.
Mix together peas and mayonnaise and spread.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise layer.
Add cheese and top with crumbled bacon.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Do not toss or mix.
Stays crisp for several days.

title: spanish rice soup
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart pot, bring water, tomato juice, rice, celery, carrots, onion and garlic to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Check occasionally to make sure there is enough liquid and add as needed, since rice absorbs liquid as it cooks.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 25 minutes more or until rice is tender.
Makes 10 servings.

title: nellie's carnation tropical freeze
directions: Chill milk in refrigerator tray until soft crystals form around edge of tray (25 or 30 minutes). Whip until stiff.
Add lemon juice; whip very stiff.
Fold sugar and orange juice into whipped mixture.
Freeze in container about 2 hours.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, boil unpeeled sweet potatoes until tender.
Remove from water and allow to cool.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice sweet potatoes.
In a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, layer sweet potato slices, apples and pecans. Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nutmeg.
Dot with butter.
Pour apple cider over top.
Bake 45 minutes or until the mixture is bubbly.

title: turtles
directions: Place caramels, milk and butter in one quart glass measure or casserole.
Heat on high for two to three minutes or until caramels are melted.

title: liverwurst dip
directions: Break liverwurst in bowl.
Mix other ingredients in.
Shape in aluminum foil.
Refrigerate.

title: chop suey hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery.
Mix ingredients, adding noodles before placing in the oven.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: In pan, melt jelly and mustard.
Stir to mix.
Add cut up hot dogs (1-inch pieces); heat until warm.
Keep warm in fondue pot or chafing dish.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and flour.
Add milk; stir over low heat until hot, but not boiling.
Beat egg yolks to break up and until light yellow.
Pour some of the hot milk mixture, slowly, into egg yolks, then pour this mixture back into saucepan and cook until slightly thickened.
Add vanilla and pour hot mixture over vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.
Beat 3 egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Slowly add 6 tablespoons sugar, beating well after each. Spoon on pudding and put in oven until lightly browned.
Serve cold.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of a double boiler or cook over low heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Cook until thick; cool.
Place between layers and on top of Lemon Cheese Cake.
Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.

title: fig cake
directions: Sift together first 7 ingredients.
Add oil, mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Add cut up fig preserves and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan on 325° for 1 hour (more if needed).

title: beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients together well.

Batter will be slightly lumpy. Pour into greased bread loaf pan. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes in preheated 350° oven. After bread has baked about 30 minutes, top may be brushed with melted butter to aid in browning.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick and easy shepherd's pie
directions: Defrost and cook hamburger in large saucepan.
Drain grease. On medium heat, add tomato soup and 3/4 can water.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 3/4 can corn.
Cook 5 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low.
Add cheese to hot mashed potatoes.
Stir until cheese is melted into potatoes. Serve tomato-hamburger mixture on top of potatoes.

title: turkey gravy
directions: Melt fat or
margarine
in
pan.
Take
from
stove and blend in flour until smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
Add 2 cups broth and cook,
stirring until you see first bubble, then the gravy is done.
Makes 2 cups.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: *If using cake mix with pudding in it, omit instant pudding; use 3 eggs instead of 4 and 1/3 cup oil instead of 1/2 cup.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese get soft.
Mix both cheeses thoroughly by hand. Add rest of ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of nuts.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs. Add mixture of flour, salt and cream of tartar; mix well.
Shape into balls. Roll in cinnamon and sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until light brown.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: nut tarts
directions: Mix 3/4 of oleo and all cream cheese.
Add flour and mix well. Divide into 24 balls.
Press each ball into miniature muffin tin. Cream 1/4 of oleo, brown sugar and egg.
Add pecans.
Put filling into crusts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
With low speed electric beater, combine sweet potatoes and butter.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in milk, syrup, salt, orange rind and vanilla.

title: crunchie chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugars, oatmeal, corn flakes, vanilla and eggs. Add in flour, baking soda, baking powder, chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry in 375° oil. Top with powdered sugar, cinnamon and sugar or leave plain.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain cherries and halve; measure juice and add water to make 1 cup.
Bring juice to a boil and dissolve gelatin in it.
Add Coke, cherries and pecans.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Bring water
to
a boil in a 12-inch Dutch oven and add bouillon
cubes.
Mix the other ingredients, except the chicken, with
the
bouillon
and water.
Lay the chicken pieces on top of the
rice
mixture.
Cook 1 1/2 hours with 12 coals on the top and
coals
on	the
bottom.
Replenish
coals as needed.

title: individual cheese balls
directions: Blend softened cheese, salad dressing, Worcestershire sauce, onion and olives.
Shape into balls.
Roll in dried beef.
Chill. Insert pretzel sticks in each ball just before serving.

title: spicy raisin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix raisins, water, brown sugar and shortening in saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; remove from heat and cool.
Add to raisin mixture the flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, baking powder, nutmeg and cloves. Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until top springs back when touched.
Cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: granny's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti noodles.
Put a layer of the noodles in the bottom of an 11x7 casserole dish.
Spread a good layer of cheese on top of the noodles.
Sprinkle a little black pepper and dot with pieces of margarine.
Repeat this for the next layer.
In a bowl, beat the eggs good then add 3 cups whole milk.
Mix good and pour over the layers of spaghetti and cheese.
It should come to the top of the cheese.
Bake at 325 degrees for about 20 - 30 minutes, until cheese browns a little on top.

title: zucchini in the skillet
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add zucchini, onion, green pepper, mushrooms and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and oregano.
Saute, stirring occasionally, on medium to low heat until zucchini is crisp and tender.

title: picante chicken grill
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over chicken.
Marinate in refrigerator for 8 hours or more.
Grill.
Serve with rice or tortillas.

title: gipshoim apple cake
directions: Peel and cut apples into thin slices.
In a well-buttered baking dish, arrange a layer of apple sections.
Sprinkle with a mixture of sugar, cinnamon and crumbs.
Add a few dots of butter to each layer.
Fill dish with alternated layers of apples and crumbs, with crumbs on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until apples are tender, about 45 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with Vanilla Sauce, whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 8 portions.

title: gold cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder into large mixing bowl.
Add shortening and 3/4 cup of milk.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add egg yolks, flavoring and remaining milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers and 35 to 40 minutes in oblong pan until surface springs back when gently touched.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients and put into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together apple filling, water and granulated sugar in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix together all the dry ingredients.
Fold the 2 together and spoon into a square baking dish that has been sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake about 30 to 40 minutes until set and golden brown on top.
This is great served warm with Dream Whip on top or nonfat frozen yogurt. Serves 9.

title: pineapple pistachio fluff(lo-cal)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Divide evenly into 4 parfait glasses.

title: broccoli and cavatelli
directions: Cook broccoli and cavatelli separately.
Combine; add olive oil to taste.
Top with cheese.

title: china soy chicken wings
directions: Chop the onions.
Mix with the soy sauce, spice, lemon juice, honey and tomato paste in a bowl.
Prick the chicken skin and coat with the sauce.
Cover and leave overnight in the refrigerator. Set the oven to 425°.
Put the coated chicken wings on a cookie sheet lined with some aluminum foil.
Keep the extra sauce!
Cook for about 45 minutes, turning them frequently and brushing with extra sauce.
They should be crisp, brown and tender.

title: christmas eve black bean soup for a crowd
directions: For every cup of dry beans, use the given proportions.
Soak beans overnight.
Cook in salted water until barely tender.
Set aside.
Slowly saute onions in olive oil.
In another pan, saute cumin in oil until it smells good.
Do not burn.
Remove onions and saute peppers.
At the last moment, add crushed garlic.
Do not burn.
Add all this to tender beans.
Add fresh squeezed lemon juice.
Add bay leaves, oregano and cilantro.
Cover and cook slowly until beans are well done.
Add more lemon juice, if needed.
This meal if filling and cheap!

title: bacon cheese potato slices
directions: Scrub potatoes and trim ends.
Cut into 3/8-inch slices. Evenly arrange on a microwave-safe plate, putting smaller slices in the center.
Sprinkle with green onion.
Cover with microwave-safe, clear plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 7 to 10 minutes, giving the dish 1/2 turn after four minutes.
Sprinkle potatoes with bacon bits, olives and cheese.
Microwave, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix crumbled Pop Tarts and melted margarine.
Press into bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan.
Combine apple pie filling, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Pour over crust (Pop Tarts).
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lasagne(mom's)
directions: Butter two 7 1/2 x 12-inch pans. Cook lasagne noodles in boiling water for 9 to 10 minutes (6 at a time). Take noodles and place a layer of macaroni on bottom of pans. Mix Ricotta cheese, milk and egg thoroughly. Then spread a layer of Ricotta cheese mixture over noodles. Spread a layer of sauce over cheese. Then sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle salt, pepper and oregano on top. Repeat layers until last layer. On last layer, spread sauce on top with oregano. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Make 3 layers in each pan.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares and store in airtight container.

title: racoon barbecue
directions: Clean the "coon" and cut into quarters.
Soak overnight in salt water.
Drain; parboil in fresh water approximately 2 hours.
Drain well; place in baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion. Mix mustard in barbecue sauce and pour over "coon."
Bake in a 300° oven for approximately 3 hours, basting during cooking period.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large iron skillet, mix the sugar and cocoa, then add milk.
On high heat, add butter and cook for 1 1/2 minutes after coming to a boil.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Stir until completely blended and drop on wax paper and cool until hardened.

title: simple beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onions, pepper, soup and water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes (approximately).

title: sweet-sour sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in vinegar, pineapple juice, green pepper, pimiento, soy sauce, garlic powder and ginger.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.

title: shrimp salad macaroni
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl adding mayonnaise (or Miracle Whip) to cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, more mayonnaise may need to be mixed in (it tends to dry out overnight).

title: peach jello salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello and stir until dissolved.
Stir in the ice cream until dissolved and let jello partially set.
Add the peach slices and let stand until firm.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: italian stuffed meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch baking pan.
Combine ground beef, oats, 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce, onion, Parmesan cheese, egg, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Mix well.
Separate mixture into patties.
Place stuffing choices on one patty.
Pinch sides together to enclose stuffing.
Smooth edges into rounded loaf. Place into pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until meat is done.
Top loaf with 1 cup spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Garnish with olives and remaining sauce.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Take the first 3 ingredients and put in heavy skillet over medium flame.
Stir constantly until mixture pulls away from sides of skillet (about 5 minutes).
Take from flame and stir in vanilla, chopped nuts, cornflakes, and Rice Krispies.
Dip hands in cold water and roll mixture into balls.
Roll balls in coconut.

title: shrimp puffs(appetizers)
directions: Mix all ingredients, drop by small teaspoonfuls in hot fat and cook until brown.
Serve hot.
Good with horseradish sauce.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream sugar and butter; beat until light and stir in egg.
Beat in bananas.
Stir these ingredients into flour mixture alternately with sour milk.
Add nuts.
Place batter in loaf pan and bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.
Test with a knife for doneness.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in sprayed casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: adirondack flapjacks
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg yolks and add milk and butter.
Stir into flour mixture until just moistened.
In small bowl beat eggs whites until stiff peaks form. Fold into batter.
In large skillet, heat 1 teaspoon oil over medium heat.
Use about 1/2 cup batter for each flapjack.
Fry until surface appears dry and bubbles form around edge.
Turn and fry on other side until done.
Remove and keep warm until all cakes have been fried, adding more oil to skillet if necessary.

title: microwave pepperoni pepitos
directions: Place chips on cookie sheet; spread out evenly.
Place one piece of pepperoni on each chip until all chips are covered.
Put a dash of taco sauce on each piece of pepperoni.
Then spread the cheeses over chips.
Place under broiler until cheeses are melted. Serve immediately.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: hot sausage patties
directions: Mix well.
Make into patties.
Separate on and between wax paper; freeze. Use as needed.
Deer meat can also be used.

title: hamburger cheese casserole
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger and chopped onion. Add salt.
When thoroughly browned, add soup and milk, stirring occasionally, until cheese sauce is smooth.
Slice potatoes and put into casserole dish.
Pour sauce over potatoes and bake in a 400° oven for 1 1/2
hours.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream shortening until
light
and fluffy.
Add cheese. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a microwave dish. Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring after each minute until slightly thickened.
Remove from microwave oven and stir in butter and vanilla.

title: special potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain the potatoes, then mash in a large bowl with an electric mixer with the sour cream and margarine.
Add the oregano and half of the grated cheese; mix well.
Spread into a baking dish; sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, or until cheese is melted.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In a bowl blend together mayonnaise and sour cream. Add pie filling and peach chunks. Spoon into lightly greased 1 quart mold or 6 individual molds and freeze until firm. Remove from molds just before serving. Serves 6.

title: pork chop potatoes
directions: Fry pork chops until well done.
Peel and slice potatoes. Place pork chops in bottom of small roaster or electric skillet. Cover with sliced potatoes.
Spoon soup and spread evenly over potatoes.
Add water and salt.
Cook on high or bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until juices are bubbly and potatoes are done.
Serves 6.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Combine chicken breasts, broth and curry powder in a medium size saucepan.
Bring to boil; simmer for 30 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Remove from heat; refrigerate without draining, allowing chicken to cool in broth for several hours.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Take 2 frozen loaves of dough.
Thaw and cut into 12 squares each (24), smaller if desired.
Put on top of topping already in pans.
Let rise; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: russian corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon. In a separate bowl, mix the cereal, milk and sugar.
Let set 5 minutes.
Add egg and applesauce. Add this to flour mixture.
Mix lightly.
Spray tins with cooking spray. Fill tins 3/4 full.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: tuna patties
directions: Chop onion and add to tuna along with egg and crushed crackers.
Pat out into patties and fry in pan.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Place in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange nut sandwiches
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Spread on ovals or rounds of whole wheat bread.
This yields about 4 dozen sandwiches.

title: pink delight
directions: Place all in blender
with
enough
ice to make mixture frothy,
as
a
frozen daiquiri.
Serve in champagne glass and garnish with a strawberry, cherry or slice of lemon.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into balls and place in greased casserole dish.
Pour soup and water over mixture.
Cover and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried cottontail rabbit!
directions: Soak a cleaned rabbit in salt and vinegar water for 8 or 10 hours.
Then cut into pieces.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Dip pieces in a beaten mixture of egg and milk, then roll each piece in cracker or bread crumbs.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and cherry fruit filling; mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes or until it springs back when lightly touched.
In a small pan, combine sugar, butter and milk. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, cook one minute.
Remove from heat and add chocolate pieces, stir until melted and smooth. Spread over cooled cake.

title: taco pie dip
directions: Brown hamburg in a skillet; drain.
Add taco seasoning mix. Add chopped onion and pepper.
Simmer until peppers and onions soften.
Put hamburg mixture into a deep pie dish.
Spread refried beans on top of the hamburg mixture.
Spread sour cream on top of the refried beans.
Sprinkle cheese all over the top.
Bake at 350° until the cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: south dakota oatmeal cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour a 9-inch square pan.
In large bowl combine oatmeal and 1 1/2 cups boiling water, cool to room temperature, stirring every 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: quick lemon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat by hand.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in powdered sugar and bake in greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix everything in the order listed. Beat well. Pour into well-greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Stir soup and cheese into cooked rice.
Drain ground beef and mix well with cheese and rice. Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato with dollops of sour cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rocky road pizza
directions: Turn oven to 375.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine with electric mixer on medium speed until softened, about 30 seconds.
Add sugar and brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well with mixer on low speed; gradually beat in flour.
Spread dough evenly in an ungreased 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake in the 375° oven about 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: In 8-quart pan, cover bottom with oil or bacon grease.
Add enough popcorn to cover bottom.
Let it get hot.
When it is about ready to pop, sprinkle 3/4 cup of sugar on top.
Cover and shake. When it is popped, remove it from pan.
VERY GOOD AND EASY.

title: huevos de queso y chile(eggs with cheese and chile)
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cheese) in large bowl with electric beater.
Fold in cheese and pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until set.
(Can be made the night before.)

title: meat loaf
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add catsup and warm water.
Stir in onion soup mix and bread crumbs.
Mix well with ground beef.
Shape into loaf or pack in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan delight tarts
directions: Cream oleo, cream cheese and flour.
Chill.
Press dough into mini-cupcake tins.
Mix eggs, sugar, 1 tablespoon oleo, pecans, vanilla and salt and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook the first 9 ingredients for 2 hours and then add the beef smoked sausage and ham.
Add water as needed.
Cook for a few more hours.
Mash beans to thicken.
Serve over rice.

title: meat-macaroni supper
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter; cook onion in butter until tender but not brown.
Stir in soup, tomatoes, cut up, dried thyme, crushed, and a dash of pepper.
Add elbow macaroni, cooked and drained, luncheon meat, cut in 1 x 1/2-inch strips, and green pepper.
Turn into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Top with shredded process American cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken after cooking.
To the eggs, add the bread, rice, milk and soup stock.
Pour into casserole. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Dilute soup with 1/2 can water.
Mix in blender. Heat until warm. Serve with chicken as gravy.
Serves 4.

title: pickle relish
directions: Grind and chop vegetables.
Cover with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Add vinegar, sugar and spices.
Cook 20 minutes. Seal.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Blend well.
Add milk (blend well).
Fold in cool whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Freeze until firm.
Take out 10 minutes before serving.
Makes two - 8 inch pies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Mix corn and soup into rice.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: kabobs
directions: Cut and put on skewers. Brush off and on with teriyaki sauce and honey on grill. Grill until meat is done.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in orange juice until smooth.
Add drained oranges.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook sausage until brown; drain and crumble.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with butter.
Line bottom of pan with crescent rolls.
Press the perforations together to seal.
Add the crumbled sausage, then the shredded cheese.

title: white cake icing(for decorating happy birthday cakes)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until creamy.
Separate desired amounts and color.

title: dilly beans
directions: Pack beans lengthwise in pint jars.
Add 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper, 1 clove garlic and head of dill to each jar.
Combine water and vinegar.
Cover beans with the mixture.
Process for 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Allow to stand for about 2 weeks to let flavor develop.

title: flaky pastry appetizers
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese and flour until blended.
Roll dough into rectangle (16 x 14) on lightly floured cloth covered board. Cut into 2-inch squares.
Place 1/2 teaspoon on one edge of each square; roll up.
Place seam side down on baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 450° or until golden brown.
Serve hot if desired. Serve with carrot sticks, cauliflowerets, celery sticks and olives.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: stuffed flounder baked
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease shallow roasting pan.
Wash fish. Pat dry.
Combine crab meat, cayenne, green pepper, mayonnaise and egg.
Place 4 pieces of fish in roasting pan.
Place 2 heaping tablespoons of crab mixture on each piece of fish.
Top with remaining fish.
Place slice of butter on each fish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Bake 30 minutes.
Baste.
Broil 5 minutes. Baste.
Broil 5 more minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill at least 1 hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; mix with others.
Pour into loaf pans. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Combine in another bowl the sugars, vanilla, butter and eggs.
Add flour mixture and stir together.
If it is too thin, add more flour. Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Cover cookie sheet with brown paper and spray with Pam.
Drop cookie dough by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Use 3 tablespoons of dough per cookie. Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes; underbake for chewy effect. Makes 2 dozen.

title: iowa corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in small skillet.
Saute green pepper and onion until tender, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs in medium size bowl.
Stir in milk.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and pepper in small cup.
Stir into egg-milk mixture.
Add cooked pepper and onion and corn.
Turn into buttered 4 to 6-cup shallow baking dish or 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a slow oven (275°) for 40 minutes or until softly set.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Put bananas in last.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zappy mac salad
directions: Cook elbow macaroni or salad macaroni according to package directions; drain well.
Cool.
(Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.

title: pat a pizza
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and milk together.
Combine with sweet potatoes.
Put in baking dish.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix all the above ingredients and place in greased regular size loaf pan.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour.
Cool completely before removing from loaf pan.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Simmer brown sugar, water, butter and vanilla in a saucepan over medium-low heat for 15 minutes.
Pour over sweet potatoes and bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hummus
directions: Blend all together; season to taste.

title: easy and good baked beans
directions: Bake at 350° until heated, about 1/2 hour.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Make cake as directed on package.
Bake in greased and floured 17 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 1-inch cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: aunt hettie's boiled dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients with milk and butter in double boiler. Heat until smooth like a white sauce.
Gradually add hot vinegar. Stir until thickened.
Pour into the beaten eggs.
Return to double boiler and cook gently.
Then strain.
Store in refrigerator.
Add a small amount of milk to thin for salad.

title: sausage-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Fry sausage and onion until light brown, drain. Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Keep stirring.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Make layers of macaroni and sausage.
Pour sauce.
Top with cheese and bake in hot oven for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: brown sugar icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Add nuts. Divide dough in half.
On a sheet of wax paper, form into rectangle approximately 12 to 14-inches long.
Wrap in paper and store in refrigerator or freezer until firm. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare noodles as directed on package. Drain. Slice olives and carrots.
Add to noodles.
Add Italian dressing to taste.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese together.
Sprinkle Jell-O over top and mix well.
Drain pineapple and oranges; mix lightly. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; chill until partially set.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Beat together.
Add corned beef, celery and onion. Fold in eggs.
Chill until firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: martha white's old-style buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse corn meal.
Stir in buttermilk with a fork until soft dough is formed. Knead and roll out on lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Cut to desired thickness.
Bake about ten minutes.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch angel food cake pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
While hot, pour glaze over cake and allow to cool in pan.

title: spicy english muffins
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter and seasonings.
Spread on cut surface of muffins.
Place muffins, buttered side up, on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes
or until golden brown.
Makes 8 halves.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and oil.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Beat well.
Pour into a large greased cookie sheet with an edge.
Bake 18 minutes at 350° or until golden.
Melt peanut butter plus margarine in double boiler. Pour over hot cake.
Melt Hershey bars and oil.
Pour over hot peanut butter.
Spread with a spoon.
Be careful not to mix with peanut butter.
Let cool.
Refrigerate until chocolate sets.

title: hearty beef pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spoon stew into 2-quart round casserole. Place pie crust directly on top of stew.
Fold edges under and flute.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Cut 2 or 3 slits in crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until crust is golden and stew is thoroughly heated.
Serves 5.

title: sugar plums
directions: Cream butter thoroughly. Add sugar slowly and continue beating until mixture is light and crumbly. Add cream and vanilla. Beat until completely blended. Shape into teaspoon sized balls and roll in colored sugar. Store in refrigerator.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix.
Let stand a while before using.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter crunchies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar and white sugar with vanilla and egg.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Make into balls; flatten with a fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
May use margarine for the shortening, but not corn oil margarine.

title: swedish fruit soup
directions: Soak fruit in water for a few minutes.
Drain and rinse. Cover with water and let simmer for 1 hour, adding 2 sticks of cinnamon, lemon and sugar.
Add 1/4 cup tapioca 20 minutes before fruit is cooked.
Stir frequently.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Put in microwave for 2 minutes.
Mix in any kind of nuts.
Drop on greased pan.
Put in fridge and cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage. Remove from stove.
Pour over Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla which has been mixed together good.
Mix well.
Put in 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: corn, noodles and cheese
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Combine remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: bean hole beans
directions: Soak beans overnight, then bring to boil and cook until skins burst when spooned.
Pour off liquid and save.
Drop a chunk of salt pork into Dutch oven, pour in beans.
Add salt, molasses and some fresh ground pepper to bean water.
Pour over beans to cover and add another chunk of pork on top.
Put on lid and set in fire pit, using hole in ground method.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In casserole dish, mix together all ingredients except cheese and bread crumbs.
Cover; cook on simmer for 10 minutes until heated, stirring once.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.

title: yummy cake and instant frosting
directions: Combine dates or raisins, water and soda; set aside to cool. Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa together and add to creamed mixture.
Add dates or raisins, water and soda mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients. Add flour and milk alternately.
Begin and end with flour.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Remember, do not preheat oven.

title: hopping john
directions: Wash and cook peas until they are tender, about 1 hour.
Add the meat and salt; cook for 1 hour.
Add rice and cook for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften	cheeses at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients. Mold
in
desired shape.
Roll in pecans and refrigerate.

title: overnight salad
directions: Place lettuce, celery, green pepper, onion and peas in layers in long baking dish.
Then mayonnaise, sugar, cheese and bacon. Refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash, quarter, core and cook apples, unpeeled, with water. Cover and simmer slowly until tender.
Rub through coarse sieve. There should be about 5 quarts pulp.
Add half as much sugar as pulp and spices.
Let simmer about 2 hours, stirring frequently. Keep a good eye on it.
It will burn easily.
When thick, pour into hot sterilized jars and seal at once.
Remember apple butter becomes stiffer when cold.
Makes 9 to 10 pints.

title: fresh fruit trifle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
Prepare, bake and cool cake following package directions for original recipe.
Cut one cake layer into 1-inch cubes. Freeze other cake layer for later use.

title: mexican salad(a meal all by itself)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add dressings last.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over pork chops.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry refrigerator cake
directions: Line spring-form pan with split ladyfingers or sliced sponge cake.
Add sugar to strawberries.
Whip the cream with vanilla. Cover cake with berries, then a layer of whipped cream.
Repeat in layers until all material is used, saving part of cream for top of cake.
Sprinkle with nuts and chill for 8 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy b & b cukes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Soak overnight in procelain or glass container.
Pack in jars and keep refrigerated.
We store in 1/2 gallon plus 1 quart jars.

title: city chicken(makes about 50 pieces; freezes well.)
directions: You will need about 50 wooden skewers, 4 1/2 to 5 inches.

title: empress beef
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice diagonally 1/4 inch wide.
Pour oil in wok or large skillet.
Heat at high for 1 minute.
Add steak and salt; stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Add snow peas, celery, mushrooms, onion and water chestnuts.
Stir-fry 3 minutes.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Combine water, soy sauce, cornstarch and sugar; stir well.
Add cornstarch mixture to beef mixture and cook
until thickened, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: dream cake
directions: Crumble angel food cake up in a large square pan or glass baking dish.
Drain 1/2 of
pineapple juice off, then pour over cake.
Next, mix sugar-free jello pudding mix with 3 cups of milk and pour over cake.
Slice bananas and put on next.
Then Cool Whip.
I usually put a few cherries on top of Cool Whip just for looks.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil until creamy.
