Add vanilla and flour. Roll into balls.
Place on lightly greased pan.
Dip bottom of glass in sugar.
Flatten cookies slightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: fettuccini
directions: In large saucepan, stir soup until smooth; blend in cream and cheese and heat, stirring frequently.
Just before serving, toss hot noodles with butter or margarine combined with soup mixture. Serve with additional cheese.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw and allow bread to rise per instructions.
Divide each loaf in half.
Roll out in oblong shape (flour counter so it will not stick).
Salt and pepper dough.
Place about 4 to 6 slices of Mozzarella cheese in center of bread.
Add several slices of pepperoni on top.
Fold over each end of dough and roll dough into bread shape.
Pinch dough underneath so cheese won't come out when cooking.
Brush top of bread with egg and water mixture.
Bake at 375° on greased cookie sheet for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Best when hot.

title: cinnamon orange butter
directions: Cream all of the ingredients together.
Serve with bread or biscuits.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bacon) in large bowl.
Pour into baking dish.
Place sliced bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger then drain fat. Add taco seasoning and water. Simmer for about 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add sour cream. Spray bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish with nonstick spray and lay a layer of tortillas on the bottom. Top with meat mixture, salsa, then cheese. You may want to make 2 layers so you end up with the cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: You will need 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Save broth.
Melt 1 stick of butter in a large skillet.
Add the box of Rice-A-Roni (including flavoring).
Lightly brown the rice.
After lightly browned, add the broth (strained) to the rice.
Simmer on low.
Tear up the chicken into bite size chunks and add to rice.
Simmer until the mixture is no longer liquid.

title: baked chocolate pudding
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients to a batter.
Cover with 1/2 cup of white sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar and the cocoa.
Mix until just mixed in.
Pour 1 cup cold water over all.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Melt butter in deep pan.
Add chocolate, flour, sugar and milk.
Boil this mixture until thickened.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters and roll into a ball.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll each ball in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Toss into a greased (Pam) Bundt pan.

title: hot ryes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bread.
Spread generously onto party rye slices.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Mix all together.
Add about 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: tater rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel, boil and mash potatoes for 1 cup. In big pot, bring to boil 1 1/2 cups water.
Add sugar, salt and yeast, making sure to dissolve.
Beat eggs gently; add to sugar and stir.
Add and dissolve shortening.
Remove pot from heat to begin to cool.
Begin to add and stir in mashed potatoes, then flour.
When dough is formed, pinch off and form into balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cover with cloth towel to allow yeast to cause dough to rise.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix ingredients; fold in egg whites.
Pour into raw pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Roll out in thin layers and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Put applesauce or apple butter between layers.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Garnish with cherries and sprinkle with more coconut (toasted).

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 25 minutes at 300° or until done. We like them a little gooey.

title: oatmeal mcgregor cake
directions: Add boiling water to oats in a small bowl, let stand 15 minutes.
Blend sugar, oil and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in oatmeal. Stir in nuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until cake tests done with a toothpick. Immediately spread with frosting and broil 3 to 5 minutes until lightly browned.

title: mex-chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients through milk in a large saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently to keep from sticking.

title: one dish casserole
directions: Season to taste.
Pour tomatoes over other ingredients and bake 1 hour and 35 minutes at 375°.

title: tomato bake
directions: In saucepan, combine tomatoes, sugar and butter. Bring to a boil, stirring often. In a bowl, combine Bisquick and milk. Drop batter on four mounds on tomatoes. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Do not lift cover while simmering. Can be doubled.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Precook and shred chicken meat.
Set aside.
Shred Monterey Jack cheese and Cheddar cheese; set aside.
Finely chop onion; set aside.
Mix together soups, chili, salsa, onion and olives; set aside.
Tear tortillas into small pieces.
Line bottom of large dish with 1/2 tortillas, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheeses. Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pina colada bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Add milk in bowl and soak. Use hands to crush bread.
Squeeze well.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Grease casserole with margarine or butter.
Pour in pudding.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until very firm.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Remove heart and bad leaves from cabbage.
Shred remaining head.
Chop celery and carrots very fine.
Mix
vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise together.
Add all dry ingredients.
Combine in a bowl with shredded vegetables.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
For best results, allow to stand overnight.

title: moist apple cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
When cool, frost with icing made by combining:

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Combine cucumbers and green onions in large bowl.
Cover; let stand for 1 hour.
Combine all remaining ingredients; pour over cucumbers.
Mix well.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: mamaw riddle's german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cocoa, eggs, vanilla, Pet milk and margarine.
Blend well, then blend in coconut, pecans and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: meat in a loaf
directions: Slice bread lengthwise.
Scoop out middle.
Reserve for dipping.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Spoon into hollowed out bread.
Wrap loaf in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Slice.
Serve hot.

title: cool and simple citrus pie
directions: Place concentrate in large mixing bowl and beat about 30 seconds.
Gradually spoon in ice cream and blend.
Fold in whipped topping and add food coloring, whipping until smooth.
Freeze if necessary until mixture will mound.
Spoon into pie crust.
Freeze until firm, at least 4 hours.
Store any leftover pie in freezer. You can also decorate top of pie with whipped cream and orange and lemon slices.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine cake mix, Jell-O and water (juice).
Blend well.
Add oil; beat well.
Add eggs, beating in one at a time.
Blend 3 to 4 minutes.
Mix in strawberries. Flour and grease pan.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 45 minutes, until done.

title: don's garlic salad(don's steak house in wichita, kansas)
directions: Put all vegetables through a food processor or blender with water, then towel dry.
Combine chopped vegetables with other ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Let set overnight.
This will be dry at first, but will become moist overnight from the water in the vegetables.
Serve cold.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients. Can use mixer.
Add egg and beat. Combine dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Press dough flat with a fork dipped in sugar. Bake in
a 325° preheated oven for 18 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: flapjacks
directions: Combine egg, milk and shortening.
Add sifted dry ingredients. Stir smooth.
Bake on ungreased griddle.
(Pour batter from a 1/3-cup measure for even size.)
Makes 9 flapjacks.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Mix together sour cream, garlic, lemon juice and celery salt. Place the chicken in a large bowl, pour the sour cream mixture over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll chicken in crumbs and place in a greased, shallow pan.
Spoon melted butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° about 40 to 60 minutes until done and crispy.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: orange jello delight
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup cold orange juice and 1 cup hot water. Mix until jello is dissolved.
It is best to mix jello with hot water and then add cold orange juice.
Add mandarin oranges (drained).
Chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: overnight crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.

title: dad's fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla.
Boil for just 2 minutes. Add vanilla and beat until it starts to harden.
Put in buttered platter or pan and let cool.

title: cooked salad dressing
directions: Mix in order given:
sugar, flour, salt and mustard.
Then add egg and milk.
Then add vinegar (add this slowly).
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add butter.
Blend thoroughly; cool.

title: no name drop cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients, plus cocoa or chocolate, if desired.
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: st. patrick's day punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add cold water.
Mix well. Add 7-Up and juice.
Add pistachio ice cream before serving.

title: creamy cheesy potato soup
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into chunks.
Cover celery, onion and potatoes with water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add soup, cheese, milk and margarine.
Simmer until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.

title: odessa apple pie
directions: With wooden spoon, mix the ingredients in order given.
Fold in raisins and apples last.
Pour mixture into a greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: date nut bar
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients together; pat half of mixture into pan.
Cook the dates, sugar and 1 cup water until thick; add 1 teaspoon vanilla and pinch of salt.
Let cool.
Add to layer in pan.
Add remainder of dry ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick apricot pie
directions: Put apricots through food chopper.
Combine fruit, water, sugar, salt, lemon juice and butter.
Bring to boil; cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Prepare pie crust according to directions; pour in filling.
Cover with strips of pastry.
Bake in moderately hot oven (425°) for 30 minutes, or until done. Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion; drain.
Add cheese and oleo while hot.
Add beaten egg, milk, crushed crackers, salt and pepper; mix all together.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with 3 crushed crackers.
Bake at 375° until brown.
This freezes nicely.

title: cauliflower with white sauce
directions: Melt the butter on low fire; add the flour and stir until blended. Add the milk and stir constantly until smooth and thickened. Add seasonings and remove from fire. Boil the prepared cauliflower in salted water for 15 or 20 minutes.
Drain; break into flowerets and put into greased casserole.
Pour over this enough white sauce to cover. Garnish liberally with bread crumbs, blended with melted butter.
Bake in moderate oven 30 minutes or until bread crumbs have browned.

title: fruit cake muffins
directions: Marinate fruits and raisins in juice overnight.
Cream sugar, butter and egg together.
Sift together flour and spices and mix with sugar mixture.
Add marinated fruit and nuts.
Spoon into muffin papers.
Top each with a cherry.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Brush tops with apple juice while warm.
Add glaze. Melt apple jelly for glaze.

title: jellied fruit salad
directions: Heat the pineapple and cherry juice.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add confectioners sugar.
Cool until slightly jelled and add other ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Blend in eggs and fruit cocktail. Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.
Pour on icing.

title: chicken lynn
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool slightly.
Pull meat away from the bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix sour cream with undiluted chicken soup and spread over chicken.
Crush crackers with hand and spread over casserole.
Melt margarine and dribble over crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly. (This can be frozen.)

title: fantastic pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except fruit. Pour into the graham cracker pie shells and top with fruit of your choice, drained. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding coconut last.
Pour in unbaked pie crust (about 9-inch size) and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring Jell-O, sugar and pineapple to boil.
Cool.
Mix buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans.
Add first mixture.
Chill for several hours.

title: rosemary roasted potatoes
directions: Mix olive oil, garlic and rosemary.
Drizzle mixture over potatoes in a flat roasting pan.
Salt and pepper.
Roast 1 hour at 400°, tossing potatoes every 20 minutes.

title: hot cheese hominy
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large skillet.
Add next 6 ingredients and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle remaining 1 cup of cheese over top.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yields 8 servings.

title: rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water in large mixing bowl. Add pinch of sugar. Add 1/3 cup sugar, warm milk, salt, shortening and slightly beaten egg. Beat 2 to 3 minutes until well beaten. Add 2 cups flour and beat 3 to 5 minutes until smooth. Add 1/2 cup flour at a time. Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. On floured surface, knead dough until smooth and elastic, about 6 minutes, adding flour as necessary to prevent sticking. Place dough in lightly greased bowl. Cover and let rise until double, 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie with glaze
directions: Mix all but jello and food coloring.
Cook over medium to medium-high heat until clear.
Remove from heat and add jello and food coloring.
Pour over strawberries that have been placed in baked pie crust.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours before eating.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt and mix well.
Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet, then remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Yields about 4 dozen cookies.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in water to cover by two inches overnight.
Drain soaking water; replace with fresh.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Add tea bags and water and boil 15 minutes.
Add lemon, orange and pineapple juices and simmer 30 minutes.

title: spareribs
directions: Saute garlic and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Cut spareribs into serving portions.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish and bake, uncovered, at 450° for 30 minutes.
Spoon part of sauce over ribs.
Reduce heat.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours and baste occasionally with remaining sauce.

title: tenth cloud cornbread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and pour in milk, oil and egg. Stir gently and don't overbeat.
Grease pan and bake at 425° until top is golden brown.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: olive mexican fiesta(serves 6)
directions: Brown the
ground
beef
with
the
onions
in	a large skillet.
Stir
in tomatoes, tomato sauce and chili sauce mix. Simmer, uncovered,	5
minutes.
Stir
in beans, corn, chilies and olives.
In a 2-quart casserole, alternately layer tortilla chips (enough
to
cover	bottom) and meat mixture, making several layers
of	each.
Sprinkle
the
top
with cheese and arrange the tortilla chips around the edge.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until bubbly hot and cheese is melted.

title: five cup salad
directions: Make a regular tossed salad with lettuce, tomatoes, sliced onion and if desired a sliced avocado.
Add 1 can drained Ranch Style or Mexican beans and 8 to 10 ounces grated Cheddar cheese. Just before serving, add Catalina salad dressing and Fritos.

title: pistachio pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except powdered sugar, with mixer on medium speed for 4 minutes. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: smoked sausage skillet("good for breakfast or dinner.")
directions: Slice smoked sausage into pieces.
Brown in skillet.
Brown hash browns in an electric skillet.
Add smoked sausage to hash browns.
Cover the top with cheddar cheese.
When cheese is melted it is done.
Makes 6 - 8 servings.
Great with eggs for breakfast or with a salad for dinner.

title: potato casserole
directions: Wash and do not peel enough potatoes to feed your family. Slice thinly, we use slicer or cheese grater.
Put into frypan with enough shortening to cover bottom.
Add salt and pepper. Cook slowly until tender.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown turkey, onion and green pepper; add tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Place biscuits in a lightly greased baking dish. Add the taco mixture and the other toppings.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon, then pour in apples.
Put in an 8-inch pie crust.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar and flour.
Cut butter mixture to make crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken continental
directions: In skillet, put sliced chicken breasts and mushrooms in butter and brown.
Stir in soup, water, parsley and dash of pepper. Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Simmer 10 minutes more or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir often.
Serves 4.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
Add sugar and stir.
Add oil and eggs; will be stiff. Add grated carrots slowly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or more in 13 x 9-inch or larger greased pan.

title: yogurt-sauced peaches
directions: In blender, combine cottage cheese, skim milk, sugar, lemon juice and cardamon.
Cover; process until smooth.
Fold in yogurt. Chill.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, add ground chuck, pepper, onion and water. Cook until pepper and onion are tender. Mix 2 cups catsup (more if needed), yellow mustard, 4 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce (or more to taste) and brown sugar. Let simmer until moisture is gone. Let simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Blend milk into mixture.
Fold Cool Whip in and pour into prepared crust.
Freeze or refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add walnuts.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat well.
Add vanilla. Bake in 3 or 4 layers at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Fry chicken in oil after you put Accent and pepper on it. Cook until done, do not brown.
Mix cream of chicken soup, curry powder and mayonnaise together.
Put asparagus on bottom of dish, spread chicken on it, then put mixture of mayonnaise over it.
Put grated cheese on top.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine peas, corn, beans, onion, celery and pimento in a 3-quart bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables, mixing well.
Marinate overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, squash and vanilla.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients which have been mixed until blended.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fettuccine carbonara
directions: Saute bacon until crisp; drain well and crumble.
Cook fettuccine according to package directions; drain well and place in warm dish large enough for tossing.
Add crumbled bacon, butter, heavy cream, grated cheese, eggs and parsley.
Toss until well coated and serve.

title: passover cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and cake meal.
Let stand awhile, then roll cookies.
Place on cookie sheet.

Can be made several ways, as you can add chocolate chips to some or all of the dough, or you can put indentation with finger and put jelly in center. You can add cinnamon to tops of some or all of the cookies.
Or you can add a little orange juice to the batter and bake in narrow pans.
Bake at 350° about 18 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add hot milk, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is thick; continue stirring.
Beat egg yolks slightly; add them to the hot liquid slowly.
(A teaspoon of vanilla flavoring can be added.)
Add butter.
Continue cooking and stirring until mixture is thick.
Cool, then put into pastry shell; cover with meringue made from egg whites.
Bake in oven at 300° to 325° until brown.

title: streusel cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix
well.	Also add dry ingredients.
Batter should be thick. Spread
of
batter
in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour
pie filling over the batter.
Add remaining batter; drop by teaspoons over top of filling.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Pour into greased loaf pans.
Sprinkle tops with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: corned beef and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles to desired doneness and drain.
Combine all ingredients and pour into prepared Pam sprayed shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sleepytime mocha mix
directions: Boil water in a cup in microwave, then add powder.

title: raisin sour cream pie
directions: Wash raisins and put in pan with 1 cup water.
Bring to boil; crumble the cracker in the sugar.
Pour into raisin mixture and simmer until thick.
After mixture has thickened, remove from heat. Gradually add egg to small amount of hot mixture.
Pour remaining ingredients into mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup sour cream.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with top crust.
Sprinkle with butter and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Bake in 3 layers.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan and add crushed pretzels and sugar.
Pat in pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes and cool. Combine Dream Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Pour over pretzel mixture.
Combine strawberry Jell-O (don't add cold water), just 2 cups boiling water, frozen strawberries and let congeal slightly. Pour over cheese mixture.
Let stand until firm.

title: oriental pasta salad
directions: Gradually add pasta bow ties to boiling water so that water continues to boil.
Cook uncovered until tender.
Drain in colander and cool.
Add snow peas, red peppers, scallions, broccoli and diced chicken.
Combine salad dressing, Tabasco, garlic powder and ginger.
Pour over pasta mixture.
Toss lightly.
Chill and enjoy.

title: quick burritos
directions: Warm each tortilla in microwave on High about 10 seconds. Spread warm tortilla (off center) with beans.
Top with meat and cheese and about 1 tablespoon of salsa.
Roll tortilla and place on plate, seam side down.
Microwave on High 25 to 30 seconds per burrito.
Top with salsa, sour cream, chopped olives or tomatoes--whatever suits you.
Yum yum and no pans to wash!
(Now that's cooking!)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour or so at 325°.

title: creamed corn
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Put in cake pans in oven.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Cool; put in freezer bags.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cover with hot water and let stand until hot through.
Pack into hot jars.
To each quart, add the listed amounts of alum, dill, pepper and garlic with a grape leaf or two. Combine vinegar, salt and water.
Heat to boiling, fill jars and seal.
Makes 6 to 8 quarts.
Put in hot water in a large pot on stove for 20 minutes or more, then remove from water.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat together until real smooth.
Bake in pie shell at 350° until pie is set.

title: easy pea salad
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients.
Cover and chill well.

title: little sugar molasses cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Mix well.
Add molasses; mix well.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Roll about 1 teaspoon of dough in a ball.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: red clam sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the butter; add the garlic, onion and celery.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, until onion and celery are tender.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, clam liquid and brandy.
Simmer sauce for 30 minutes.
Stir in the clams and parsley.
Heat thoroughly and pour over prepared linguine.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Good used as a dip for fresh vegetables.

title: sinful chocolate chip nut tart
directions: Let refrigerated pie crust sit at room temperature according to package directions.
Ease pastry into an 11-inch tart pan with removable bottom.
Trim pastry even with the rim of the pan.
Do not prick pastry.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oranges, eggs and oil.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed of mixer.
Reduce to low and beat 1 minute.
Pour batter into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.

title: "pittsburgh special"
directions: Mix chili sauce and jelly together.
Add vinegar and cooked kielbasa
(sliced into bite size sections).
Heat in crock-pot on high to the heat of your choice.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Cool mixture to room temperature.
Bring water and the rest of the salt (2 teaspoons) and oil to a boil. Add acini de pepe until done.
Drain and rinse and cool to room temperature.
Combine egg mixture and acini de pepe.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Refrigerate until chilled. The salad can be refrigerated for as long as 1 week in an airtight container or it can be frozen, but it might alter the texture. Makes about 25 servings.

title: super punch
directions: Mix juices and ginger ale with 1/2 of the ice cream.
Spoon into glasses; add a glob of ice cream on top.
Or mix all together and serve.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt together bars, marshmallows and milk.
Beat whipping cream and fold in chocolate mixture.
Pour into graham cracker or vanilla wafer crust.
Refrigerate overnight or until firm.

title: cajun stuffed eggplant
directions: Place eggplant halves in large pot of boiling water, salted. Boil 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove from water and drain, cut side down, on wire racks.
Scoop out pulp, being careful not to break skin.
Reserve shells.
Cut scooped out portion into 1/2-inch cubes, set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towel to cool, then crumble and reserve.
In same skillet, cook onion, green pepper, celery and garlic 5 minutes or until tender.
Add pork and beef; cook 5 minutes longer or until browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in eggplant cubes, bacon, chopped tomatoes, Tabasco sauce, thyme, oregano and salt; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in bread crumbs and 1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon mixture in shells.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until eggplant is heated through and cheese is lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip
the cream cheese that has softened with the brown sugar. Add
pecans and vanilla.
Chill.
Very good with apple slices.

title: yummy fudge bars
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.

Add butter and mix until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumbs. Press remainder of crumbs into a greased 13 x 9 pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Remove from the oven. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil and add 1 cup M&M's. Cook on low heat, stirring constantly and pressing chocolate pieces to break them up. Remove from heat and stir in Eagle Brand milk. Mix well, then spread over partially baked crust, leaving a 1/2-inch border. Combine remaining crumbs and remaining M&M's; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add eggs.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Add salt to flour and sift.
Combine all ingredients and roll out and cut in shapes or spoon onto cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Place a pecan half in the center.
Bake in 300° oven for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: curried corn and sweet red peppers
directions: Melt butter in medium skillet; add red pepper and cook, stirring constantly until tender.
Stir in corn and next 3 ingredients; cook, stirring often for 3 minutes.
Stir in whipping cream; cook, stirring constantly just until thoroughly heated. Serve alone or over chicken breasts or sliced pork tenderloin. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in fourths.
Cover with water; boil until tender.
Drain off water.
Add butter and milk.
Mix with electric mixer.
If potatoes are too thick, add milk until you get right consistency.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and vegetables.
Have ready.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add flour, salt, saffron and pepper. Stir until blended.
Add broth.
Cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Place chicken and vegetables in casserole dish.
Pour thickened mixture over chicken and vegetables.
Cover with crust.

title: magic marshmallow crescent puffs
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip marshmallows in melted butter; roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Wrap a crescent triangle around each, completely covering marshmallow and squeezing edges of dough tightly to seal.
Dip in butter; place in muffin pans. Put on foil and bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Immediately remove; drizzle with glaze.
Sprinkle with nuts. Makes 16 rolls.

title: apple crisp
directions: With fingers, mix all ingredients and 4 tablespoons of melted butter until crumb form.
Arrange 4 cups of chopped apples in a 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle mixture over apples. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Trim fat off meat.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Cover the roast with all the ingredients.
Cover pan with foil. Bake 4 hours at 325°.
